1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,070
The most entertaining suspense
that predicts love.

2
00:00:03,070 --> 00:00:05,070
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

3
00:00:05,070 --> 00:00:08,960
Five people with sharp romance
radars have gathered.

4
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:10,470
[The panel of five people is here]

5
00:00:10,470 --> 00:00:12,600
We aren't sharp at all.

6
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:15,380
- The week felt so long.
- I couldn't wait.

7
00:00:15,380 --> 00:00:16,580
The week was long.

8
00:00:16,580 --> 00:00:20,620
Last week, they chose one person and asked

9
00:00:20,620 --> 00:00:22,240
them out directly on a date.

10
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:24,520
The first was Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong's date.

11
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:27,300
- I kept having doubts.
- You felt anxious about Wu Yeol?

12
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:29,330
Yes, I felt that way a bit.

13
00:00:29,330 --> 00:00:34,460
But the nice thing was that
Yu Gyeong had taken the lead.

14
00:00:34,460 --> 00:00:38,180
She was letting aggression out,
but in a playful way.

15
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:42,320
And every single word Yu Gyeong said

16
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:45,690
crushed Wu Yeol's heart a little bit.

17
00:00:45,690 --> 00:00:47,350
You already are beyond my reach.

18
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:51,310
I think the date went well because
she has given up a little.

19
00:00:51,310 --> 00:00:54,200
And Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri's Gangneung date.

20
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:58,470
It felt like Wu Yeol was
ending things with Gyu Ri.

21
00:00:58,470 --> 00:00:59,960
I was like, "He's going that far?"

22
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:01,940
It made me think that.

23
00:01:01,940 --> 00:01:03,400
He seemed like a different person.

24
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:06,000
There have been many beach dates
on Heart Signal.

25
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,010
I've never seen anyone
with their hands on their back.

26
00:01:08,010 --> 00:01:11,010
- Ahem.
- What was with that pose?

27
00:01:11,010 --> 00:01:14,040
And there was a new meaningful date.

28
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:15,680
Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong's date.

29
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:18,790
It was planned just for Yu Gyeong
from start to finish.

30
00:01:18,790 --> 00:01:19,980
It was cool.

31
00:01:19,980 --> 00:01:22,210
If she were my daughter,

32
00:01:22,210 --> 00:01:24,940
I would be like, "It's Jun Hyeon."

33
00:01:24,940 --> 00:01:27,530
- He's so stable.
- After the date,

34
00:01:27,530 --> 00:01:30,950
we thought he would end up
just as a good oppa.

35
00:01:30,950 --> 00:01:34,010
But while talking to the other
women, Yu Gyeong seemed...

36
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:36,270
a bit affected by the date.

37
00:01:36,270 --> 00:01:38,480
I'm so torn.

38
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:39,540
It was nice...

39
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:43,630
We thought Yu Gyeong was set on Wu Yeol.

40
00:01:43,630 --> 00:01:44,720
We don't know anymore.

41
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:48,790
I thought Jun Hyeon might become more daring.

42
00:01:48,790 --> 00:01:52,640
That would make Wu Yeol pursue
Yu Gyeong more aggressively.

43
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,700
- It's getting more interesting.
- He totally would.

44
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:57,510
And Seo Won and So Yun's date.

45
00:01:57,510 --> 00:02:00,360
- Theirs was the most romantic.
- It was exciting.

46
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:01,930
It was the most romantic.

47
00:02:01,930 --> 00:02:03,900
It had the excitement of a first date.

48
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:05,800
It was like they were getting
to know each other.

49
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:08,750
It was like they were on a blind date.

50
00:02:08,750 --> 00:02:11,410
Like they just met and wanted
to get to know each other.

51
00:02:11,410 --> 00:02:12,470
It felt like that.

52
00:02:12,470 --> 00:02:16,960
Seo Won has always been casual on dates.

53
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,250
He's just been nice.

54
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:22,080
But his feelings toward So Yun surfaced.

55
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:24,840
We saw him feeling nervous and flustered.

56
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:27,600
- Like a little girl.
- That's a very good thing.

57
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:31,730
So Yun talks very directly, too.

58
00:02:31,730 --> 00:02:33,710
I don't think I have anyone but you.

59
00:02:33,710 --> 00:02:35,980
That must've gotten him flustered.

60
00:02:35,980 --> 00:02:38,220
He's never been treated like that before.

61
00:02:38,220 --> 00:02:40,880
And her smiley eyes, too.

62
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:43,600
I love those two.

63
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:52,020
[They are sitting in the living room]

64
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:06,740
- There's a lot going on.
- Must be stressful.

65
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:08,540
[A few days ago]

66
00:03:08,540 --> 00:03:10,860
It hurts my feelings.

67
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:13,450
Do you actually want to
go on a date this weekend?

68
00:03:13,450 --> 00:03:15,270
Let's have fun.

69
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:17,710
[They promised to go on a date]

70
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:21,120
I know you hate me.

71
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,950
No, I like you.

72
00:03:22,950 --> 00:03:25,510
It's not that I'm not interested.

73
00:03:26,270 --> 00:03:28,040
[They ran into each other
while on separate dates]

74
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:29,810
What are you doing here?

75
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:34,270
I heard you were sobbing.

76
00:03:34,270 --> 00:03:35,900
Didn't you cry?

77
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,420
We didn't cry.

78
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:41,490
Gosh, I can't talk to Ts.

79
00:03:41,490 --> 00:03:44,170
Doesn't thinking about that make you cry now?

80
00:03:44,170 --> 00:03:46,150
How could you not cry?

81
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:49,150
I think that's how true lovers should be.

82
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:53,010
They were like,
"You'll do well no matter what."

83
00:03:53,010 --> 00:03:55,320
- The unconditional...
- Trust?

84
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:59,640
You have faith and support
for the other person, no matter what.

85
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,630
I think that's love.

86
00:04:01,630 --> 00:04:03,490
I was so sad.

87
00:04:06,230 --> 00:04:08,810
Breaking up is part of love.

88
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,910
I'm scared.

89
00:04:12,650 --> 00:04:14,680
I have a break-up phobia.

90
00:04:15,930 --> 00:04:17,690
You cry, don't you?

91
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,820
I totally cry.

92
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:24,800
I'm going crazy.

93
00:04:27,790 --> 00:04:30,340
[Seo Won is checking the time]

94
00:04:30,850 --> 00:04:32,400
Should I go to sleep?

95
00:04:34,830 --> 00:04:37,290
What? Why are you covering your mouth?

96
00:04:37,290 --> 00:04:39,120
[Jun Hyeon just finished Self Talk]

97
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:41,120
Why are you covering your mouth?

98
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,480
I don't think Seo Won will come out today.

99
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,820
I thought of him as soon as I sat down.

100
00:04:46,670 --> 00:04:48,610
I don't think he'll come out today.

101
00:04:48,610 --> 00:04:50,350
Don't cry, Oppa.

102
00:04:50,350 --> 00:04:52,280
I don't cry anymore.

103
00:05:00,210 --> 00:05:03,280
- He keeps checking on her.
- He is.

104
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:07,250
This calls for scolding.

105
00:05:08,030 --> 00:05:11,780
- Hyung, you should discipline them.
- Yes, you're the oldest.

106
00:05:17,210 --> 00:05:20,220
I feel like they might not come home.

107
00:05:22,470 --> 00:05:25,310
- What a mess.
- Yeah...

108
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:28,330
I think they both went home.

109
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:31,580
They went home
because it's the Lunar New Year?

110
00:05:31,580 --> 00:05:34,280
- It's the Lunar New Year.
- I'm not sure about Wu Yeol,

111
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:38,070
- but I think Gyu Ri might've.
- Instead of stopping by here,

112
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:40,750
she could have gone straight home.

113
00:05:42,430 --> 00:05:46,470
- You're right.
- Just leave her be.

114
00:05:46,470 --> 00:05:49,670
- This makes things harder.
- It's okay to go to Gangneung.

115
00:05:49,670 --> 00:05:53,240
Just think they left at 1:00 a.m.

116
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,720
Around 1 a.m.

117
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:02,480
[Seo Won is lost in thought]

118
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,720
[Smiling]

119
00:06:05,770 --> 00:06:07,920
This is tasty.

120
00:06:09,530 --> 00:06:11,270
Come on.

121
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:13,900
I feel like she's my daughter. Come here.

122
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:16,190
My baby.

123
00:06:17,060 --> 00:06:19,280
Unni.

124
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:23,250
You sound like a cow.

125
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:30,030
[After finishing talking in Gangneung]

126
00:06:30,940 --> 00:06:33,390
Really? Are they driving separately?

127
00:06:33,390 --> 00:06:35,540
[They decided to go back separately]

128
00:06:35,540 --> 00:06:38,450
What? They're coming back separately?

129
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:42,200
What happened?

130
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:56,150
[Wu Yeol sent the text
for the day on his way back]

131
00:06:59,340 --> 00:07:03,140
[Yu Gyeong is back in the room]

132
00:07:05,130 --> 00:07:07,520
I've been meaning to talk to you.

133
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:09,410
- I...
- Come on.

134
00:07:09,410 --> 00:07:11,750
In this...

135
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:13,690
[Their conversation after the truth game]

136
00:07:13,690 --> 00:07:17,740
I thought of you the most in that situation.

137
00:07:17,740 --> 00:07:21,720
Because of our dates and the things I said.

138
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:24,860
When we saw the movie together,

139
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:28,400
it became clear that it was you.

140
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:32,770
For that reason, I don't think I should.

141
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:36,260
I've been wanting to make it clear to Gyu Ri.

142
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:41,000
All of my fingernails are broken.

143
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:44,350
Help me.

144
00:07:44,350 --> 00:07:47,890
- The knife...
- I used the knife.

145
00:07:47,890 --> 00:07:50,000
What if I hurt my wrist?

146
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:03,140
What's going on?

147
00:08:07,580 --> 00:08:10,510
[It's hard to overcome...]

148
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:12,180
I left mine in the car.

149
00:08:13,380 --> 00:08:15,840
[the fear]

150
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:17,480
What do we do?

151
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:19,000
What?

152
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:22,040
No, no. Why, why?

153
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,440
[Does trusting mean...]

154
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:34,980
But I haven't seen what the others are like
when they're actively pursuing me.

155
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:36,680
[trusting the other person?]

156
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:39,790
Is 70-80% that significant?

157
00:08:39,790 --> 00:08:41,050
[Or...]

158
00:08:41,050 --> 00:08:43,690
That's my biggest question.

159
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:48,490
[is it about trusting yourself?]

160
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:59,420
[Salt Bread: Let's enjoy our remaining time]

161
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:07,120
[Got a message from Wu Yeol]

162
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,830
Aigoo.

163
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:18,440
I realized that I must like Yu Gyeong a lot.

164
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:20,940
What I thought was correct.

165
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:24,890
I didn't want to be so direct with you.

166
00:09:24,890 --> 00:09:28,430
That's why I've been beating around the bush.

167
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:34,250
I didn't want to say this, but...

168
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:39,780
I didn't think it'd end otherwise.
That's why I'm saying it.

169
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:42,350
I think that's crucial.

170
00:09:42,350 --> 00:09:45,510
So? What's the conclusion?

171
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:50,220
It means I've already decided.

172
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:52,980
I'm not saying this because I'm drunk.

173
00:09:52,980 --> 00:09:54,890
I didn't even drink much.

174
00:09:58,540 --> 00:10:00,080
[Beluga of the Forest: I had fun.
Don't be sick and feel better.]

175
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:03,290
Yu Gyeong got a text from Beluga.

176
00:10:08,090 --> 00:10:09,700
[My Dog, Yellow: Thank you so much for today]

177
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:13,650
- He got a text from Yellow.
- "Thank you so much for today."

178
00:10:13,650 --> 00:10:16,780
[Yu Gyeong also texted Jun Hyeon]

179
00:10:16,780 --> 00:10:18,160
[Seo Won didn't get a text
from Gyu Ri tonight]

180
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:20,360
Oh, my God.

181
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:24,420
[Gyu Ri texted Wu Yeol]

182
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:31,320
[Pure Rabbit]

183
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:33,320
- She texted him.
- So Yun.

184
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:39,840
He didn't get a text
from the person he wanted.

185
00:10:47,540 --> 00:10:51,220
[Leave a message for the person
you are thinking about the most]

186
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:06,220
Well...

187
00:11:08,490 --> 00:11:10,510
Gyu Ri.

188
00:11:13,260 --> 00:11:18,180
I don't know how impactful
your date tonight was.

189
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:24,050
On the last day, both you and I could

190
00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:28,450
miss each other.

191
00:11:29,830 --> 00:11:32,820
But I hope you're always happy. So...

192
00:11:36,590 --> 00:11:39,410
let's enjoy our last few days.

193
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:44,370
I miss you a bit today.

194
00:11:45,660 --> 00:11:47,860
That's all.

195
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:50,480
He left a message only for Gyu Ri.

196
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:04,650
He sat back down.

197
00:12:06,470 --> 00:12:10,100
[Seo Won is not able
to leave the Self Talk Room]

198
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:12,940
Someone's here.

199
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:17,060
He's here. He's here.

200
00:12:23,420 --> 00:12:25,000
[Everyone is asleep]

201
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,710
Everyone's sleeping.

202
00:12:30,310 --> 00:12:35,450
He's anxious because he doesn't know
how she felt before going to sleep.

203
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:40,540
[Wu Yeol has trouble falling asleep]

204
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:44,040
- He doesn't feel so good, either.
- Of course not.

205
00:12:56,260 --> 00:13:02,160
[Around 4 a.m.]

206
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:07,090
[Glancing]

207
00:13:22,620 --> 00:13:27,300
[Yu Gyeong left the house early]

208
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:33,760
- I started the laundry.
- Really?

209
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:37,370
- Who's home right now?
- There are four men.

210
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,850
There are four men.

211
00:13:39,850 --> 00:13:42,770
There are two men in each room.

212
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:46,870
I don't know if Yu Gyeong left.
She's not here.

213
00:13:46,870 --> 00:13:49,700
- So Yun, Gyu Ri, and Min Ju.
- Are they here?

214
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:52,750
[Yu Gyeong is gone for the day]

215
00:14:13,810 --> 00:14:17,140
[Gets back into bed]

216
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,470
Can you show me what you shot earlier?

217
00:14:21,470 --> 00:14:23,700
- Which one? The video?
- Yes.

218
00:14:24,390 --> 00:14:26,460
Look at this.

219
00:14:27,780 --> 00:14:29,040
Do you know what this is?

220
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:31,110
Want to take a selfie?

221
00:14:34,650 --> 00:14:36,480
Let's take one like this.

222
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:40,860
- How? How?
- In wide angle.

223
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:43,420
- I'm supposed to do this, right?
- Yes.

224
00:14:43,420 --> 00:14:47,120
No, no. Hold on. Give it to me.

225
00:14:49,110 --> 00:14:50,730
CCTV.

226
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:12,260
I didn't want to meet you.

227
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:16,300
If we didn't meet back then...

228
00:15:17,210 --> 00:15:18,890
You know...

229
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:25,380
Things would've changed a lot, right?

230
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:31,570
[I sincerely hope you find your other half]

231
00:15:31,570 --> 00:15:35,470
- When did you write that? In the morning?
- Late last night.

232
00:15:36,490 --> 00:15:38,410
That woke me up.

233
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:43,620
It had an impact.

234
00:15:44,690 --> 00:15:48,630
I put it quietly in my bag
without showing emotion.

235
00:15:56,760 --> 00:16:00,390
[He wonders how Yu Gyeong feels right now]

236
00:16:00,390 --> 00:16:06,150
[Min Ju's tipping point]

237
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:14,730
There's something I want to say to Seong Min.

238
00:16:14,730 --> 00:16:23,450
He told me about romantic versus
human connection toward someone.

239
00:16:23,450 --> 00:16:30,580
I want to thank him
for sharing his honest feelings.

240
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:36,830
- I love the night view in Seoul.
- Wow, what a great view.

241
00:16:36,830 --> 00:16:41,280
I know. Timing has always been on our side.

242
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:43,210
You're right.

243
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:45,790
I was looking at the plant today.

244
00:16:45,790 --> 00:16:46,960
The plant?

245
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:49,710
Really? Good job.

246
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:53,120
It definitely helps. It really does.

247
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:57,370
- Did you put it at the hospital?
- Yes, I didn't have time to stop by home.

248
00:16:57,370 --> 00:16:59,010
Good job.

249
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:04,100
[A restaurant in Namyangju]

250
00:17:06,620 --> 00:17:09,820
- I'm glad they sell non-alcoholic beer here.
- I know.

251
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,150
Does it taste different? How is it?

252
00:17:11,150 --> 00:17:15,800
I'm curious because I've never chugged beer.

253
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:19,050
Why... Why are you so cute?

254
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:23,710
What was the thing you were curious about?

255
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:26,006
I've been wanting
to talk about this with you.

256
00:17:26,006 --> 00:17:27,140
What is it?

257
00:17:27,140 --> 00:17:31,270
You probably became curious
about stuff after the truth game.

258
00:17:31,270 --> 00:17:34,650
- The truth game had a huge impact.
- It was the most important thing.

259
00:17:34,650 --> 00:17:38,250
I've been wanting to go on a date with you.

260
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:41,780
- Right, we needed to talk.
- True.

261
00:17:41,780 --> 00:17:44,780
It might not be such a big deal.

262
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:46,130
What is it?

263
00:17:46,130 --> 00:17:49,020
- She's not looking at him while he talks.
- You know...

264
00:17:49,020 --> 00:17:53,010
The first impression and feelings.

265
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:56,430
You said you're 50-50
between Min Ju and Yu Gyeong.

266
00:17:56,430 --> 00:18:00,880
- This is important.
- To be honest, whenever I see you,

267
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:06,560
your head points toward Yu Gyeong.

268
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:08,710
I've noticed stuff like that.

269
00:18:08,710 --> 00:18:12,710
- She's telling him very directly.
- I'm glad she's telling him.

270
00:18:12,710 --> 00:18:15,160
My feelings toward Yu Gyeong
were much stronger at first.

271
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:17,690
But I've been going on dates with Min Ju.

272
00:18:17,690 --> 00:18:20,970
Whenever I talk to her,
I notice we have a lot in common.

273
00:18:20,970 --> 00:18:24,320
I realized I had feelings for her, too.

274
00:18:28,210 --> 00:18:31,310
So I thought it was 50-50. I feel that way.

275
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:33,850
It must be if that's how you feel.

276
00:18:33,850 --> 00:18:36,780
So Yun takes no nonsense.

277
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:43,570
[Getting water
while sorting out his thoughts]

278
00:18:50,490 --> 00:18:52,270
[Sipping]

279
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:58,660
They talked about romantic
connection versus a human connection.

280
00:18:58,660 --> 00:19:00,380
When I heard that...

281
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:05,850
I find you obviously very easy to talk to.

282
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:08,800
There's this energy I get
when I'm with you, too.

283
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:12,690
But on the other hand, I think...

284
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:18,320
I felt more connected to you as a person.

285
00:19:19,070 --> 00:19:20,640
Hold on.

286
00:19:21,430 --> 00:19:25,390
I don't think I knew either, but...

287
00:19:26,580 --> 00:19:32,100
I think my feelings for Yu Gyeong
were more romantic.

288
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:36,420
It looked similar from the outside.

289
00:19:36,420 --> 00:19:40,260
I didn't understand
why I kept acting differently.

290
00:19:40,260 --> 00:19:43,490
I wasn't sure, but while talking to So Yun...

291
00:19:43,490 --> 00:19:45,860
- You realized it?
- I think I did.

292
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:54,440
I realized I didn't know myself at all.

293
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:57,020
- You realized it yesterday?
- I did.

294
00:19:57,020 --> 00:20:01,670
And you decided to talk to me about it today.

295
00:20:01,670 --> 00:20:07,220
[Seong Min carefully revealed his feelings]

296
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:12,690
Yeah, you can.

297
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:15,960
[After that]

298
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:23,810
[They started their day separately]

299
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:26,800
[Sitting]

300
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:36,750
I'm so happy that
you're being honest with me.

301
00:20:39,370 --> 00:20:42,490
You like me as a person,

302
00:20:42,490 --> 00:20:44,190
but I have romantic feelings for you.

303
00:20:44,190 --> 00:20:47,900
So, I'm definitely upset, but...

304
00:20:49,010 --> 00:20:51,730
accepting that is also...

305
00:20:51,730 --> 00:20:56,940
You had many dates with someone
you just liked as a person.

306
00:20:56,940 --> 00:20:59,080
I felt the butterflies.

307
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:02,640
I did get butterflies.
That actually confused me a lot.

308
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:04,320
I was like, "What's this?"

309
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:14,420
Thankfully, I've been aware
of that to a certain extent.

310
00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:19,010
I don't feel too hurt or upset.

311
00:21:19,010 --> 00:21:23,060
[She's been noticing Seong Min's feelings]

312
00:21:23,060 --> 00:21:25,170
Let me smack you after this.

313
00:21:25,850 --> 00:21:28,270
Let me smack you just once.

314
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:34,330
I'll listen to the Interstellar
soundtrack before bed.

315
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:42,780
[That's how the conversation ended]

316
00:21:51,450 --> 00:21:53,030
[Notices Seong Min]

317
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:54,680
I'm going for a walk. Want to join me?

318
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:56,940
A walk? Shall we?

319
00:21:58,140 --> 00:22:00,080
You have to go out on a day like this.

320
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:03,520
Right, we need to refresh our moods.

321
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:06,660
- Are you in a bad mood?
- No, I'm not.

322
00:22:06,660 --> 00:22:09,670
- Are you feeling stressed?
- No, I'm not.

323
00:22:09,670 --> 00:22:11,970
I'm totally fine.

324
00:22:11,970 --> 00:22:14,510
I'm an adult.

325
00:22:14,510 --> 00:22:16,850
You sure are an adult.

326
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:21,820
Seong Min seemed to be having a hard time.

327
00:22:21,820 --> 00:22:23,730
He cries at work, apparently.

328
00:22:23,730 --> 00:22:27,550
I did think he must be suffering
as much as I.

329
00:22:27,550 --> 00:22:28,510
[Han River]

330
00:22:28,510 --> 00:22:31,920
- What? It's so pretty.
- Isn't it pretty?

331
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:34,210
- Aren't you glad we came out?
- I am.

332
00:22:34,210 --> 00:22:37,150
[Han River unveils itself]

333
00:22:37,150 --> 00:22:40,740
Han River is so pretty. It's something else.

334
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:44,760
- It's so wide open.
- I love it.

335
00:22:44,760 --> 00:22:46,980
- Aren't you glad we came out?
- I am.

336
00:22:46,980 --> 00:22:48,870
Doesn't it make you feel so much better?

337
00:22:48,870 --> 00:22:51,430
Being here makes me want to run.

338
00:22:51,430 --> 00:22:53,770
Want to run? Should we run to the cafe?

339
00:22:53,770 --> 00:22:56,700
- Let's run!
- Should we?

340
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:02,560
- Whatever, let's run. This is nice.
- Isn't it nice?

341
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:06,840
- It relieves stress.
- It really helps.

342
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:17,120
After I told you that yesterday,

343
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:20,550
I didn't realize... It's so windy.

344
00:23:20,550 --> 00:23:24,360
- Are you suddenly confessing something?
- No, it's not that.

345
00:23:27,030 --> 00:23:29,440
I feel much more at ease.

346
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:30,910
You feel at ease?

347
00:23:30,910 --> 00:23:34,500
I feel much more at ease here,
but it's so windy.

348
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:37,000
- Maybe we should talk again in the car.
- What? Hold on.

349
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,440
What do you want to talk about?

350
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:41,970
I feel comfortable. I'm enjoying this moment.

351
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:47,560
- Why would he tell her that?
- Min Ju must feel so sad to hear that.

352
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:57,170
I'm glad you're feeling at ease.

353
00:23:58,460 --> 00:24:00,720
- What about you?
- Me, too.

354
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:04,220
I'm relieved to hear that. That's nice.

355
00:24:04,220 --> 00:24:07,680
- Wow! How could you, Seong Min?
- Seriously.

356
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:11,590
Let's go to the car. It's very windy.

357
00:24:14,110 --> 00:24:17,760
- The hair is so...
- I really want to run.

358
00:24:21,660 --> 00:24:23,450
Daebak.

359
00:24:25,290 --> 00:24:26,350
[They're back at the house]

360
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:27,980
Is everyone gone?

361
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:35,770
- What do we do?
- Even I'm upset.

362
00:24:39,040 --> 00:24:48,320
[Lost in her thoughts on her own]

363
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:49,860
He shouldn't have said that.

364
00:24:49,860 --> 00:24:53,250
He's totally drawing a line
by saying he feels at ease.

365
00:24:53,250 --> 00:24:56,190
Why would he tell her that?

366
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:04,090
[Min Ju is heading somewhere]

367
00:25:04,090 --> 00:25:06,520
Who is she meeting?

368
00:25:06,520 --> 00:25:08,910
What? This is a new person.

369
00:25:11,670 --> 00:25:13,050
She must be a friend.

370
00:25:13,050 --> 00:25:16,610
Why is this so funny? Seriously.

371
00:25:16,610 --> 00:25:19,710
Unni. Unni...

372
00:25:19,710 --> 00:25:21,070
[Her sister whom she hasn't seen in a while]

373
00:25:21,070 --> 00:25:24,300
- It's Min Ju's older sister.
- This is so funny.

374
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:25,570
Why did you lose so much weight?

375
00:25:25,570 --> 00:25:28,640
- Unni, I've had a hard time.
- Min Ju...

376
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:30,330
She did lose weight.

377
00:25:30,330 --> 00:25:31,500
It's on me.

378
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:33,560
- She's pretty.
- They're both cute.

379
00:25:33,560 --> 00:25:35,730
It's nice to see you.

380
00:25:35,730 --> 00:25:37,670
Thank you.

381
00:25:38,350 --> 00:25:40,160
[Kim Gyu Ri, Kim Min Ju's older sister]

382
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:43,560
- Her sister is so chic.
- She's beautiful.

383
00:25:44,340 --> 00:25:46,720
I really missed you.

384
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:49,620
She's my best friend.

385
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:52,950
We support each other more than anyone else.

386
00:25:52,950 --> 00:25:57,800
She's like a friend
who always fully supports me.

387
00:25:57,800 --> 00:25:59,800
Her parents have such beautiful daughters.

388
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:01,800
I changed my background photo.

389
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:05,750
- We put our legs together.
- So cute.

390
00:26:05,750 --> 00:26:09,980
The third person to move in...

391
00:26:09,980 --> 00:26:11,820
must have been Seong Min.

392
00:26:11,820 --> 00:26:15,430
- Who's Seong Min?
- Seong Min is...

393
00:26:16,630 --> 00:26:19,830
She liked Seong Min from the beginning.

394
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:26,520
[Staring]

395
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:31,100
I find Seong Min the easiest to talk to.

396
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:35,310
He was so eloquent,
and he tried to lift the mood.

397
00:26:35,310 --> 00:26:37,300
Do you have feelings for him?

398
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:39,110
Huh? Yes. How did you know?

399
00:26:39,110 --> 00:26:42,470
- Your ideal type is someone you can talk to.
- Right.

400
00:26:42,470 --> 00:26:44,580
What? Why are you so shocked?

401
00:26:44,580 --> 00:26:47,930
- I know everything about you, Min Ju.
- As expected of her sister.

402
00:26:47,930 --> 00:26:51,900
- To me, your ideal type is...
- You're right.

403
00:26:51,900 --> 00:26:53,960
Does his looks...

404
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,480
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

405
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:58,170
Wow, it looks good.

406
00:26:59,540 --> 00:27:00,700
So?

407
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:02,610
[Try this]

408
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:05,230
Why don't you have more?

409
00:27:07,890 --> 00:27:11,890
What about him? Is your person...

410
00:27:11,890 --> 00:27:13,760
- He's two years older than me.
- Why are you so shy?

411
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:14,900
Why is she still shy?

412
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:16,840
- What's the deal?
- He was born in '98.

413
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:18,530
He's a year younger than you.

414
00:27:18,530 --> 00:27:21,060
I'm not shy. I just...

415
00:27:21,060 --> 00:27:23,180
Does he like you, too?

416
00:27:26,210 --> 00:27:27,740
Gosh...

417
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:33,220
I wouldn't have lost weight if he did.

418
00:27:34,950 --> 00:27:37,840
I would've gained weight
because I would've been happy.

419
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:39,710
Hold on.

420
00:27:39,710 --> 00:27:40,610
[Cracking]

421
00:27:40,610 --> 00:27:44,330
- Whoa, your bones cracked.
- The back of my neck hurts.

422
00:27:44,330 --> 00:27:47,730
Why is that? Does he have a unique type?

423
00:27:47,730 --> 00:27:49,420
Unique type...

424
00:27:51,500 --> 00:27:54,450
He said he had feelings for two people.

425
00:27:54,450 --> 00:27:58,750
He said it was me and someone else.

426
00:27:58,750 --> 00:28:02,190
We plan to go to a restaurant in Namyangju.

427
00:28:02,190 --> 00:28:05,300
We went there and while we ate...

428
00:28:09,790 --> 00:28:12,440
He said he likes me as a person.

429
00:28:15,230 --> 00:28:16,630
[Tap]

430
00:28:16,630 --> 00:28:17,920
Wow, she's...

431
00:28:17,920 --> 00:28:20,290
- What does that mean?
- He likes me as a person.

432
00:28:20,290 --> 00:28:24,240
He has romantic feelings for someone else.

433
00:28:25,610 --> 00:28:28,240
He's so honest.

434
00:28:28,240 --> 00:28:29,910
Yes.

435
00:28:31,140 --> 00:28:34,830
Did you not cry? Do you cry every night?

436
00:28:35,730 --> 00:28:40,450
I don't cry every night, but I'm upset.

437
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:43,090
Gosh.

438
00:28:43,810 --> 00:28:46,910
- Min Ju.
- Every day has been a struggle.

439
00:28:46,910 --> 00:28:49,430
Min Ju!

440
00:28:49,430 --> 00:28:51,350
- I don't cry.
- Why do I feel sad?

441
00:28:51,350 --> 00:28:52,540
Why are you sad?

442
00:28:52,540 --> 00:28:53,940
[Choked up]

443
00:28:55,410 --> 00:28:59,060
- Why are you sad?
- I'll get us some tissues, Min Ju.

444
00:28:59,060 --> 00:29:01,220
[Tearing up]

445
00:29:06,550 --> 00:29:08,630
I'm losing weight, Unni.

446
00:29:09,630 --> 00:29:11,670
She's going through a lot.

447
00:29:14,180 --> 00:29:20,010
But actually, it's okay because
when we were talking about it,

448
00:29:21,010 --> 00:29:23,610
I felt serene.

449
00:29:29,090 --> 00:29:31,560
I actually felt totally okay.

450
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:35,440
- So...
- You must really like him.

451
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:37,830
Yes, so...

452
00:29:37,830 --> 00:29:40,870
But he said it was 50-50.

453
00:29:40,870 --> 00:29:45,330
That gives me hope because I'm 50.

454
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:53,410
I was happy that I was 50.

455
00:29:53,410 --> 00:30:01,460
The truth game
let me enjoy my last days here...

456
00:30:01,460 --> 00:30:02,725
Oh, my.

457
00:30:02,725 --> 00:30:06,485
We're not family and we're torn.
Imagine her sister.

458
00:30:09,270 --> 00:30:13,870
- I finally got to see you, but why am I sad?
- Well...

459
00:30:13,870 --> 00:30:17,280
It's because our hearts are synced up.

460
00:30:17,280 --> 00:30:21,460
I noticed how much weight
you lost all this time.

461
00:30:22,210 --> 00:30:25,140
You seem to have a lot on your mind.

462
00:30:25,140 --> 00:30:27,170
To be honest...

463
00:30:28,520 --> 00:30:32,420
there's nothing
I could have said to him then.

464
00:30:35,180 --> 00:30:38,390
- This is nuts.
- I don't find stuff like that hurtful.

465
00:30:38,390 --> 00:30:41,400
I find small things hurtful.

466
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:46,570
After I told you that yesterday,
I feel much more at ease.

467
00:30:46,570 --> 00:30:48,140
You feel at ease?

468
00:30:48,140 --> 00:30:50,840
Yes, that was hurtful.

469
00:30:54,020 --> 00:30:56,720
He must find you very easy to be around.

470
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:58,960
That must be why he keeps
revealing his true feelings.

471
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:01,640
Why does he keep revealing his true feelings?

472
00:31:01,640 --> 00:31:04,940
I know. That's exactly my point.

473
00:31:07,740 --> 00:31:09,030
Yu Gyeong?

474
00:31:09,030 --> 00:31:10,950
- You want me to get her?
- Please.

475
00:31:10,950 --> 00:31:15,790
Yu Gyeong, Seong Min wants me to get you.

476
00:31:17,790 --> 00:31:21,310
You asked if you should get her
for him, and he said yes?

477
00:31:21,310 --> 00:31:22,880
I said, "You want me to get Yu Gyeong?"

478
00:31:22,880 --> 00:31:25,420
And if he said, "No, I'm here to see you."
That would've been weirder.

479
00:31:25,420 --> 00:31:26,970
- Is that so?
- She's defending him.

480
00:31:26,970 --> 00:31:29,200
I'm just really upset.

481
00:31:31,430 --> 00:31:33,340
I'm just really upset.

482
00:31:33,340 --> 00:31:36,430
It's okay. You have to be honest here.

483
00:31:36,430 --> 00:31:38,790
We can't help it.

484
00:31:38,790 --> 00:31:41,910
You've been hurt many times already.

485
00:31:41,910 --> 00:31:43,670
Even before he told you that.

486
00:31:43,670 --> 00:31:46,640
She gets it because she's her sister.

487
00:31:49,260 --> 00:31:53,120
I just don't want you to get hurt.

488
00:31:55,780 --> 00:31:58,000
Why do I keep tearing up?

489
00:31:59,820 --> 00:32:04,260
I don't want you to get hurt
too much as your sister.

490
00:32:04,260 --> 00:32:05,930
Right.

491
00:32:07,940 --> 00:32:10,680
To be honest, I'm still mad at him.

492
00:32:10,680 --> 00:32:15,190
I shouldn't feel hurt
since that's how he feels.

493
00:32:15,190 --> 00:32:21,050
I wonder if he even understands
my devotion and sincere feelings

494
00:32:21,050 --> 00:32:24,710
I've been displaying for him.

495
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:33,910
Anyway, you're cool, Min Ju.

496
00:32:33,910 --> 00:32:35,960
I couldn't have been like you if I were you.

497
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:39,290
I would have been like,
"Anyone out there who likes me?"

498
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:40,950
Really?

499
00:32:40,950 --> 00:32:47,270
Seong Min... He needs to be
taught a lesson after this.

500
00:32:47,270 --> 00:32:50,520
I wish you had come here with him.

501
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:53,580
- He might be giving you a stink eye.
- Me?

502
00:32:53,580 --> 00:32:56,420
I don't know. Maybe so.

503
00:32:56,420 --> 00:32:58,010
[A moment to heal the hurt feelings]

504
00:32:58,010 --> 00:33:00,480
Min Ju really needed this.

505
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:04,660
I'm about to tear up, too.

506
00:33:04,660 --> 00:33:07,620
Seriously, that was too...

507
00:33:07,620 --> 00:33:10,060
She suggested going for a walk

508
00:33:10,060 --> 00:33:11,920
and got her feelings hurt even more.

509
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:14,320
That was so hurtful.

510
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:17,160
There was no need for him to say that.

511
00:33:17,160 --> 00:33:21,670
He said he felt at ease
after their chat yesterday.

512
00:33:21,670 --> 00:33:23,330
Shouldn't Min Ju be saying that instead?

513
00:33:23,330 --> 00:33:27,190
He's the one who farted.
Shouldn't he apologize?

514
00:33:27,190 --> 00:33:29,790
I realized this
after their morning conversation.

515
00:33:29,790 --> 00:33:32,750
He said he likes her as a person,
not romantically.

516
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:34,540
He doesn't seem to think of it
as a rejection.

517
00:33:34,540 --> 00:33:38,250
He thinks he just told her that
he likes her as a person.

518
00:33:38,250 --> 00:33:40,670
- Is he a foreigner?
- A foreigner wouldn't say that.

519
00:33:40,670 --> 00:33:42,820
Is his Korean that bad?

520
00:33:42,820 --> 00:33:45,690
Tsuki doesn't make mistakes like that.

521
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:47,710
Your Korean is better.

522
00:33:47,710 --> 00:33:51,910
He doesn't know
that she's hurt by what he said.

523
00:33:51,910 --> 00:33:53,550
Oh, my God.

524
00:33:53,550 --> 00:33:56,300
It was so sad when her sister
pointed out something.

525
00:33:56,300 --> 00:33:59,580
When she heard about Seong Min
asking for Yu Gyeong,

526
00:33:59,580 --> 00:34:01,820
Min Ju actually defended him.

527
00:34:01,820 --> 00:34:06,680
And she said, "You must have been
hurt many times already."

528
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:07,990
- She knew.
- Seriously.

529
00:34:07,990 --> 00:34:10,910
That's why she was so okay with that.

530
00:34:10,910 --> 00:34:14,710
I didn't think she was suffering so much.

531
00:34:14,710 --> 00:34:18,740
We haven't seen her crying
or revealing strong emotions.

532
00:34:18,740 --> 00:34:23,200
She suddenly started crying
while talking to her sister.

533
00:34:23,200 --> 00:34:25,630
I think she'll try to move on now.

534
00:34:25,630 --> 00:34:27,140
I know exactly how this feels.

535
00:34:27,140 --> 00:34:30,240
After floundering at the bootcamp,
you saw your mom's face.

536
00:34:30,240 --> 00:34:31,390
Exactly.

537
00:34:31,390 --> 00:34:33,230
Everyone cries when they see
their mom after the training.

538
00:34:33,230 --> 00:34:36,710
After the mock battles and
jumping with a parachute,

539
00:34:36,710 --> 00:34:38,270
you saw your mom.

540
00:34:38,270 --> 00:34:41,830
Talking to her sister would
help her be objective.

541
00:34:41,830 --> 00:34:45,800
"I am really hurt. This isn't right."

542
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:47,900
I hope she realizes that.

543
00:34:47,900 --> 00:34:50,820
Let's go eat. I'm hungry.

544
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:56,420
The back is tight. I'll pull forward.

545
00:34:57,220 --> 00:34:59,130
Wow, what's this?

546
00:35:02,230 --> 00:35:04,370
Get in. Let's go. Let's go eat.

547
00:35:04,370 --> 00:35:06,840
- Wow, how nice.
- That's so nice.

548
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:09,820
I put some snacks in the middle.

549
00:35:09,820 --> 00:35:12,680
- There are a lot of jellies in here.
- I put some in there.

550
00:35:12,680 --> 00:35:14,250
Let's each have one.

551
00:35:15,020 --> 00:35:18,500
- I'll put one in your mouth.
- Thank you.

552
00:35:18,500 --> 00:35:20,630
[On their way while sharing snacks]

553
00:35:20,630 --> 00:35:22,280
How much will you guys drink tonight?

554
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:24,070
A lot.

555
00:35:24,070 --> 00:35:27,220
- All the way?
- Not that much.

556
00:35:28,220 --> 00:35:30,010
- This is it, right?
- Yes.

557
00:35:31,010 --> 00:35:35,880
[They already arrived at the destination]

558
00:35:36,590 --> 00:35:38,780
- Daebak.
- That place looks nice.

559
00:35:38,780 --> 00:35:40,690
So atmospheric.

560
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:43,820
So warm.

561
00:35:43,820 --> 00:35:46,100
This place is the real deal.

562
00:35:46,100 --> 00:35:48,180
It really is.

563
00:35:48,180 --> 00:35:50,340
- How about steamed cuttlefish?
- That's a must.

564
00:35:50,340 --> 00:35:51,610
- Would you like that?
- I love it.

565
00:35:51,610 --> 00:35:54,630
Should we get a pancake
since it's Lunar New Year?

566
00:35:54,630 --> 00:35:56,080
How about a meat pancake?

567
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:59,360
- Should we get started?
- Shall we?

568
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:00,170
[Clank]

569
00:36:04,890 --> 00:36:06,860
It's nice.

570
00:36:06,860 --> 00:36:10,260
I'm in trouble.
I think I'm in trouble tonight.

571
00:36:10,260 --> 00:36:13,400
- You can tell from the first glass.
- He's feeling it.

572
00:36:14,440 --> 00:36:18,160
I'm so happy I have you guys.
I mean it, Hyung.

573
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:21,040
Wu Yeol acts like the youngest
among the guys.

574
00:36:22,420 --> 00:36:24,010
Jun Hyeon's favorite.

575
00:36:24,010 --> 00:36:30,340
It feels different to bring
you guys to my regular spot.

576
00:36:30,340 --> 00:36:33,030
- The vibe adds a lot.
- It's his regular spot.

577
00:36:33,030 --> 00:36:35,890
- How nice.
- Should I just pour you some?

578
00:36:35,890 --> 00:36:37,800
- Hi.
- Hi.

579
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:39,850
- What's the deal?
- I'm here.

580
00:36:39,850 --> 00:36:40,800
He's here.

581
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:43,480
- Why would you like? Did you have dinner?
- No.

582
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:46,100
- Get whatever you want.
- What should I get?

583
00:36:46,100 --> 00:36:48,730
Let's drink first. Let's drink, guys.

584
00:36:48,730 --> 00:36:51,280
- Let's be casual between us.
- Okay.

585
00:36:51,280 --> 00:36:53,640
- Okay.
- Let's drink.

586
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:55,560
- Good work today.
- Good work.

587
00:36:55,560 --> 00:36:58,400
- This is great.
- Look at the four men.

588
00:37:00,040 --> 00:37:04,030
- We're finally hanging out, the four of us.
- It took us a long time.

589
00:37:04,030 --> 00:37:06,060
- I've been waiting for this moment.
- I know.

590
00:37:06,060 --> 00:37:08,440
Let's die tonight.

591
00:37:08,440 --> 00:37:10,440
Really? Can you handle it?

592
00:37:10,440 --> 00:37:14,790
- Seo Won did come late.
- Have some more.

593
00:37:14,790 --> 00:37:16,950
Why don't you drink the rest of it, Seo Won?

594
00:37:16,950 --> 00:37:19,250
- What?
- Penalty drink?

595
00:37:19,250 --> 00:37:20,860
I'd love it. Thank you.

596
00:37:20,860 --> 00:37:22,740
Should we all drink together? Cheers.

597
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:24,430
- For your health.
- For your health.

598
00:37:24,430 --> 00:37:26,300
Happy New Year, Seo Won.

599
00:37:27,840 --> 00:37:30,250
We have to play Yunnori*.
(Korean traditional board game)

600
00:37:30,250 --> 00:37:31,800
I know.

601
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:33,910
So Yun is picking up a used set.

602
00:37:33,910 --> 00:37:35,280
She's picking it up? Really?

603
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:39,170
A Yunnori set was 1,000 won.

604
00:37:39,170 --> 00:37:43,960
- Just drink half.
- Why would you drink just half?

605
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:46,900
Thank you.

606
00:37:48,640 --> 00:37:51,400
How do you think one should love, Hyung?

607
00:37:51,400 --> 00:37:53,790
Love? With heart, of course.

608
00:37:53,790 --> 00:37:55,720
- What about you?
- Love is techniques.

609
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:57,410
Have you seen my book?

610
00:37:57,410 --> 00:37:59,070
- What about you?
- Me?

611
00:37:59,070 --> 00:38:01,600
- I need to think.
- No, don't think.

612
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:04,640
I came this far without thinking.

613
00:38:04,640 --> 00:38:06,070
That's why I'm in this mess.

614
00:38:06,070 --> 00:38:08,470
That caused me so many tears, too.

615
00:38:08,470 --> 00:38:10,930
Did you think I had a personality like this?

616
00:38:10,930 --> 00:38:12,710
No, I had no clue.

617
00:38:12,710 --> 00:38:15,250
Your personality? I noticed it a little bit.

618
00:38:15,250 --> 00:38:17,120
When we first met,

619
00:38:17,120 --> 00:38:20,700
you kept making attempts like this.

620
00:38:20,700 --> 00:38:22,300
I could tell you were naughty.

621
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:24,580
I wondered why you were trying to be quiet.

622
00:38:24,580 --> 00:38:26,470
Did you try to be quiet at first?

623
00:38:26,470 --> 00:38:29,200
Not exactly. I was feeling so shy.

624
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:32,250
- He's totally needed here.
- He's indispensable.

625
00:38:32,250 --> 00:38:35,470
That's what I think. When I first came,

626
00:38:35,470 --> 00:38:37,890
I would've been lost without Seo Won.

627
00:38:37,890 --> 00:38:40,630
I love your dimples.

628
00:38:40,630 --> 00:38:43,710
- He made me feel comfortable.
- Right, right.

629
00:38:43,710 --> 00:38:46,080
Wu Yeol had zero interest in me.

630
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:48,480
He mentioned this from the beginning.

631
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:50,590
He was far away with Yu Gyeong.

632
00:38:50,590 --> 00:38:52,800
He was cold at first.

633
00:38:53,910 --> 00:38:56,070
I was looking at Yu Gyeong.

634
00:38:58,200 --> 00:39:00,650
- Hold on. Hold on.
- Should we drink?

635
00:39:00,650 --> 00:39:02,930
Has it started? Has it started?

636
00:39:02,930 --> 00:39:05,640
I was just being honest.

637
00:39:05,640 --> 00:39:08,720
The three are awkward because
they still like Yu Gyeong.

638
00:39:08,720 --> 00:39:10,630
It seemed that way.

639
00:39:10,630 --> 00:39:13,600
Wu Yeol? On the first day?

640
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:15,840
No, when you first came.

641
00:39:15,840 --> 00:39:18,760
Everyone else looked at me.

642
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:20,450
- But Wu Yeol...
- He didn't look at all?

643
00:39:20,450 --> 00:39:23,040
He didn't look at me even
when he was supposed to.

644
00:39:23,040 --> 00:39:24,610
- On purpose.
- Yeah, on purpose.

645
00:39:24,610 --> 00:39:26,100
Was he covering his eyes?

646
00:39:26,100 --> 00:39:30,100
- Be honest, isn't that true?
- I looked at you.

647
00:39:30,100 --> 00:39:34,490
We didn't make eye contact,
but I was looking at you.

648
00:39:34,490 --> 00:39:36,670
- No, that's not true.
- Come on now!

649
00:39:36,670 --> 00:39:38,810
- That's not true.
- We have video evidence.

650
00:39:38,810 --> 00:39:42,160
- I kept looking at you like this.
- Come on now!

651
00:39:42,160 --> 00:39:43,790
Like this?

652
00:39:43,790 --> 00:39:47,330
[He seemed uninterested]

653
00:39:47,330 --> 00:39:50,550
- He looked at him.
- He did look at him.

654
00:39:54,620 --> 00:39:56,750
You'll know when you watch it later.

655
00:39:56,750 --> 00:39:58,400
I looked at you.

656
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:01,490
- This looks good. I'm glad we got it.
- Look how good it looks.

657
00:40:01,490 --> 00:40:04,640
I know, it's a real soondae.

658
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,280
A photographic proof.

659
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:08,250
Isn't this great?

660
00:40:08,250 --> 00:40:10,990
- It's too far away.
- I can't help my long arms.

661
00:40:10,990 --> 00:40:12,520
Let's take a selfie.

662
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:15,550
I'll get four text messages.

663
00:40:15,550 --> 00:40:17,200
You're too greedy.

664
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:20,280
- I wanted that to happen once, but it won't.
- Just give me one.

665
00:40:23,070 --> 00:40:25,150
There's something I've been curious about.

666
00:40:25,150 --> 00:40:28,180
I want to ask since we're all here.

667
00:40:28,180 --> 00:40:33,900
What was the most memorable moment or date?

668
00:40:33,900 --> 00:40:35,470
- Mine is the same.
- What?

669
00:40:35,470 --> 00:40:37,230
My first date with Min Ju.

670
00:40:37,230 --> 00:40:42,120
It was at a cafe
on our first date in Tokushima.

671
00:40:43,090 --> 00:40:45,120
Sitting by that clock?

672
00:40:45,120 --> 00:40:47,200
[They exchanged honest feelings]

673
00:40:49,540 --> 00:40:52,820
Who was your first choice then?

674
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:55,170
My first choice was Yu Gyeong.

675
00:40:55,170 --> 00:40:57,100
It still is now.

676
00:40:57,100 --> 00:40:59,670
- Really?
- When we were in Japan, too?

677
00:40:59,670 --> 00:41:01,160
Really? I had no idea.

678
00:41:01,160 --> 00:41:03,060
I had no idea, either.

679
00:41:03,060 --> 00:41:08,030
- They don't know when they're in there.
- I don't know how any of you felt then.

680
00:41:08,030 --> 00:41:09,580
No one knew back then.

681
00:41:09,580 --> 00:41:12,550
- Because we watch it from here, right?
- It's not the same.

682
00:41:12,550 --> 00:41:14,860
Was it Yu Gyeong from the beginning?

683
00:41:14,860 --> 00:41:19,790
I... I noticed something a few days ago.

684
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:24,940
I was romantically drawn to Yu Gyeong.

685
00:41:24,940 --> 00:41:27,610
And I was drawn to Min Ju as a person.

686
00:41:27,610 --> 00:41:31,530
That's when I realized it. I didn't know
because I like them both.

687
00:41:32,300 --> 00:41:35,250
What was your most memorable moment?

688
00:41:35,250 --> 00:41:37,890
Let's see. The most memorable one was

689
00:41:37,890 --> 00:41:40,930
my date with Yu Gyeong in Japan.

690
00:41:40,930 --> 00:41:42,970
Everyone brings up Yu Gyeong.

691
00:41:42,970 --> 00:41:47,490
When we had dinner after the art museum.

692
00:41:47,490 --> 00:41:54,620
That was when I revealed my
true feelings for the first time.

693
00:41:54,620 --> 00:42:01,940
I just think I've been noticing you the most.

694
00:42:01,940 --> 00:42:03,880
That's how I feel.

695
00:42:06,190 --> 00:42:09,530
Remember what we talked about the day before.

696
00:42:09,530 --> 00:42:12,470
Who should I go on a date with tomorrow?

697
00:42:12,470 --> 00:42:14,930
Who do you want, Hyung?

698
00:42:14,930 --> 00:42:16,440
Me?

699
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:17,730
Yu Gyeong.

700
00:42:17,730 --> 00:42:20,400
Tomorrow will be our last day in Japan.

701
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:21,690
You're right.

702
00:42:21,690 --> 00:42:23,850
Tomorrow is very important.

703
00:42:23,850 --> 00:42:27,920
We might have to leave it to luck.
It's a one-in-four chance.

704
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:30,330
But I don't want to leave it to luck.

705
00:42:31,010 --> 00:42:34,540
I said that to Yu Gyeong that evening.

706
00:42:34,540 --> 00:42:35,850
To Yu Gyeong?

707
00:42:35,850 --> 00:42:40,270
Up until then, I asked out the person

708
00:42:40,270 --> 00:42:42,660
I hadn't talked to before.

709
00:42:42,660 --> 00:42:45,370
That was my priority.

710
00:42:45,370 --> 00:42:49,430
But I chose her in Japan
for a different reason.

711
00:42:49,430 --> 00:42:52,290
I just wanted to tell her that.

712
00:42:52,290 --> 00:42:55,980
I didn't ask her out because
I haven't had a date with her.

713
00:42:55,980 --> 00:42:58,120
There was a different reason.

714
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:05,122
I was being honest with her in that moment.

715
00:43:05,122 --> 00:43:07,224
You told her how you feel for the first time.

716
00:43:07,224 --> 00:43:09,172
That's why it's memorable.

717
00:43:11,905 --> 00:43:14,190
Wu Yeol has a lot on his mind.

718
00:43:14,190 --> 00:43:16,500
- What about you, Wu Yeol?
- Me?

719
00:43:17,270 --> 00:43:19,160
- The most memorable moment?
- Yes.

720
00:43:19,160 --> 00:43:21,850
Do you want a drink? Want to drink and talk?

721
00:43:21,850 --> 00:43:23,500
Cheers.

722
00:43:32,480 --> 00:43:35,780
I've mentioned this before.

723
00:43:35,780 --> 00:43:37,600
The movie theater date.

724
00:43:37,600 --> 00:43:40,560
- Right.
- That was a powerful moment.

725
00:43:42,650 --> 00:43:44,200
But it's been updated.

726
00:43:44,200 --> 00:43:46,960
- Really?
- I've changed my mind, too.

727
00:43:48,120 --> 00:43:49,830
Mine was the other day.

728
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:56,290
When I went on a date with Yu Gyeong.

729
00:43:57,870 --> 00:44:01,610
[His latest date with Yu Gyeong]

730
00:44:03,770 --> 00:44:07,620
I almost went up to 60%. Sorry...

731
00:44:07,620 --> 00:44:09,800
At the time...

732
00:44:12,200 --> 00:44:16,580
I was feeling guilty toward her
even that morning.

733
00:44:17,340 --> 00:44:19,970
I wasn't sure how I was going to

734
00:44:19,970 --> 00:44:24,330
face her if we were going on a date that day.

735
00:44:24,330 --> 00:44:30,930
I wasn't sure how she would treat me, either.

736
00:44:30,930 --> 00:44:33,070
But when we were actually on the date,

737
00:44:34,180 --> 00:44:35,970
we were the same as usual.

738
00:44:35,970 --> 00:44:43,050
We were both in a better mood than usual.

739
00:44:45,020 --> 00:44:49,990
The dates have always been nice,

740
00:44:51,020 --> 00:44:54,360
but I think our date that day
was the most impactful.

741
00:44:54,360 --> 00:44:58,550
- Yu Gyeong did a good job on that date.
- She did great.

742
00:45:00,510 --> 00:45:03,610
Let's have a drink. Cheers.

743
00:45:03,610 --> 00:45:05,170
This is nice.

744
00:45:05,170 --> 00:45:08,490
[They shared honest feelings]

745
00:45:10,120 --> 00:45:12,570
We have four to five days left.

746
00:45:14,210 --> 00:45:19,730
I'm not looking forward
to anything in particular.

747
00:45:23,760 --> 00:45:28,690
I'll just be honest about
my thoughts and feelings.

748
00:45:28,690 --> 00:45:32,500
- I'll just follow my heart.
- Of course.

749
00:45:32,500 --> 00:45:36,140
- Wherever your heart leads you?
- Yes.

750
00:45:36,140 --> 00:45:39,640
- I'm planning to be selfish, to be honest.
- Yes.

751
00:45:41,910 --> 00:45:48,050
Instead of thinking about the other person,

752
00:45:49,940 --> 00:45:51,800
I can just follow my heart.

753
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:53,650
- That's important.
- Sounds good.

754
00:45:53,650 --> 00:45:57,710
- He has no expectations.
- Since there isn't much time left.

755
00:46:01,080 --> 00:46:05,880
Great. Let's try our best
to leave no regrets.

756
00:46:09,210 --> 00:46:11,150
Isn't the word "selfish" exciting?

757
00:46:11,150 --> 00:46:13,600
He's saying,
"I won't think about you, Wu Yeol."

758
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:16,160
The important thing is that
Wu Yeol's gaze changed.

759
00:46:16,160 --> 00:46:18,820
He said, "I liked her since Japan.

760
00:46:18,820 --> 00:46:20,970
My feelings will stay the same."

761
00:46:20,970 --> 00:46:24,700
Unlike before, Wu Yeol's eyes began to shake.

762
00:46:24,700 --> 00:46:27,610
Jun Hyeon had many dates with her recently.

763
00:46:27,610 --> 00:46:30,740
And nobody dislikes Jun Hyeon.

764
00:46:30,740 --> 00:46:34,510
He must've thought Yu Gyeong
might start looking at him.

765
00:46:34,510 --> 00:46:35,720
I think he felt a bit threatened.

766
00:46:35,720 --> 00:46:39,050
There are only four to five days left.

767
00:46:39,050 --> 00:46:42,290
He was like,
"These guys like Yu Gyeong, too?'

768
00:46:42,290 --> 00:46:46,320
He must've thought things are
going well with Yu Gyeong,

769
00:46:46,320 --> 00:46:48,810
but he shouldn't get too comfortable.

770
00:46:48,810 --> 00:46:51,590
Wu Yeol mentioned his latest date.

771
00:46:51,590 --> 00:46:54,680
He was like,
"I'm the one who's the closest to her."

772
00:46:54,680 --> 00:46:57,170
- There's that, too.
- Ever since the tea room,

773
00:46:57,170 --> 00:47:01,870
he must have realized that he likes her more.

774
00:47:01,870 --> 00:47:04,760
He likes her a lot right now.

775
00:47:04,760 --> 00:47:08,250
That's why he's feeling nervous right now.

776
00:47:08,250 --> 00:47:11,720
Jun Hyeon isn't an easy competition.
Man to man.

777
00:47:11,720 --> 00:47:14,940
She could have had as much fun with him.

778
00:47:14,940 --> 00:47:16,870
Totally.

779
00:47:16,870 --> 00:47:19,640
[Late at night]

780
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:23,000
When are the men coming home?

781
00:47:23,000 --> 00:47:26,300
Yunnori sounds fun.

782
00:47:26,300 --> 00:47:28,220
Yunnori is fun.

783
00:47:28,220 --> 00:47:30,680
- Let's go, Hyungnim.
- Thank you.

784
00:47:30,680 --> 00:47:32,550
So cold.

785
00:47:32,550 --> 00:47:35,800
- What?
- Is our Blackpink here?

786
00:47:35,800 --> 00:47:37,970
Blackpink?

787
00:47:37,970 --> 00:47:40,290
- You're all totally drunk.
- Why are you alone?

788
00:47:40,290 --> 00:47:41,470
Do you want ice cream?

789
00:47:41,470 --> 00:47:43,270
- Tell me the flavor you want.
- Mint chocolate.

790
00:47:43,270 --> 00:47:45,980
- I want mint chocolate.
- He wants mint chocolate. And?

791
00:47:45,980 --> 00:47:47,990
- I want "Mom is an Alien."
- Alien.

792
00:47:47,990 --> 00:47:49,490
- Others are upstairs?
- Yes.

793
00:47:49,490 --> 00:47:50,780
- Is everyone here?
- Yes.

794
00:47:50,780 --> 00:47:52,350
- All four.
- Yes.

795
00:47:54,160 --> 00:47:55,460
[The second floor is filled with laughter]

796
00:47:55,460 --> 00:47:56,770
What's going on?

797
00:47:56,770 --> 00:47:58,290
He paused while walking upstairs.

798
00:47:58,290 --> 00:48:00,820
What's with them? What's going on?

799
00:48:01,900 --> 00:48:03,370
Hi, Seo Won.

800
00:48:03,370 --> 00:48:04,770
Hi.

801
00:48:04,770 --> 00:48:07,280
We just came home, too.

802
00:48:07,280 --> 00:48:08,850
Hi.

803
00:48:09,680 --> 00:48:11,370
You all drank a bit.

804
00:48:11,370 --> 00:48:13,160
We wanted to drink more.

805
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:16,030
We drank six or seven bottles.

806
00:48:16,030 --> 00:48:17,540
- Soju?
- Just soju. Right?

807
00:48:17,540 --> 00:48:19,740
- What ice cream do you want?
- I want Alien.

808
00:48:19,740 --> 00:48:21,490
[Staring]

809
00:48:21,490 --> 00:48:24,020
[Everyone is in the house]

810
00:48:25,110 --> 00:48:27,360
- Did you see Yunnori?
- I did.

811
00:48:27,360 --> 00:48:28,870
He keeps lurking.

812
00:48:29,650 --> 00:48:32,330
- What's this? Who is this?
- It's mine.

813
00:48:32,330 --> 00:48:35,800
Is it the gift you bought for everyone?

814
00:48:35,800 --> 00:48:37,950
I regret it.
I should have only given it to women.

815
00:48:37,950 --> 00:48:39,100
You gave everyone?

816
00:48:39,100 --> 00:48:42,010
I spent over 100,000 won since
I got it for everyone.

817
00:48:42,010 --> 00:48:43,100
160,000 won?

818
00:48:43,100 --> 00:48:45,960
- How much? 160,000 won?
- It was 38,000 won each.

819
00:48:45,960 --> 00:48:47,840
You spent about 300,000 won.

820
00:48:48,620 --> 00:48:51,100
Yu Gyeong won't look at him right now.

821
00:48:51,100 --> 00:48:52,590
[It got quiet]

822
00:48:55,560 --> 00:48:59,010
- Wu Yeol is anxious.
-He's walking on thin ice.

823
00:48:59,680 --> 00:49:03,890
But Wu Yeol hasn't told her that
he ended things earlier.

824
00:49:03,890 --> 00:49:07,390
Did you really get a hot pot?
Tell me everything you did.

825
00:49:07,390 --> 00:49:09,060
Why? What are you curious about?

826
00:49:09,060 --> 00:49:12,460
I just want to know what you did.

827
00:49:15,030 --> 00:49:17,390
Wu Yeol isn't feeling great.

828
00:49:17,390 --> 00:49:21,520
- He did a great job.
- It was a rejection of the century.

829
00:49:21,520 --> 00:49:23,590
We had hot pot and chatted a bit.

830
00:49:24,300 --> 00:49:27,820
Why are you so curious?
Want to go to the tea room?

831
00:49:27,820 --> 00:49:29,540
No.

832
00:49:31,230 --> 00:49:32,570
How many bottles did you have?

833
00:49:32,570 --> 00:49:34,600
One and a half bottles per person.

834
00:49:34,600 --> 00:49:36,300
[The scarf they made in Japan]

835
00:49:36,300 --> 00:49:37,950
When are we taking these home?

836
00:49:37,950 --> 00:49:39,620
That's what I'm saying.

837
00:49:40,400 --> 00:49:43,260
- I thought it turned into a decoration.
- I know.

838
00:49:44,430 --> 00:49:46,630
- We don't need to talk, right?
- What?

839
00:49:46,630 --> 00:49:48,060
We don't need to talk, right?

840
00:49:48,060 --> 00:49:51,270
- What do you mean?
- We don't need to go on a date.

841
00:49:52,980 --> 00:49:54,450
Wu Yeol is next to her.

842
00:49:54,450 --> 00:49:56,140
Long time no see.

843
00:49:57,240 --> 00:49:59,600
[Yu Gyeong is amazing]

844
00:49:59,600 --> 00:50:00,810
She's above him now.

845
00:50:00,810 --> 00:50:02,770
The hierarchy shifted.

846
00:50:02,770 --> 00:50:04,380
Amazing.

847
00:50:05,700 --> 00:50:07,090
Long time no see.

848
00:50:07,090 --> 00:50:09,260
He's in her face.

849
00:50:09,260 --> 00:50:10,410
Was that too harsh?

850
00:50:10,410 --> 00:50:14,070
Why is it so hard to see your face?

851
00:50:14,070 --> 00:50:16,180
You know whose fault it is.

852
00:50:17,140 --> 00:50:19,050
Have you been well?

853
00:50:19,050 --> 00:50:24,090
Yu Gyeong is scary. The first thing
she said was, "Long time no see."

854
00:50:24,090 --> 00:50:26,480
- Should we talk a bit?
- We don't...

855
00:50:26,480 --> 00:50:28,390
I think you two need to talk.

856
00:50:28,390 --> 00:50:31,730
Later. I'm sure we'll get a chance.

857
00:50:31,730 --> 00:50:34,870
- Yu Gyeong is confident now.
- There's no later anymore.

858
00:50:34,870 --> 00:50:38,240
She has her hands in her pockets now.

859
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:42,610
- Let's talk here.
- We need to play Yunnori.

860
00:50:42,610 --> 00:50:44,210
Just for a moment.

861
00:50:44,210 --> 00:50:47,510
- Just talk here.
- I know. Why try to push me away?

862
00:50:47,510 --> 00:50:49,670
I'm doing the dishes. Could you
bring me that cup over there?

863
00:50:49,670 --> 00:50:51,500
You really want to talk?

864
00:50:52,220 --> 00:50:54,950
- Okay.
- Wu Yeol's behavior changed a lot.

865
00:50:54,950 --> 00:50:58,400
Isn't it uncomfortable? Are you cold?
You are still wearing your puffer.

866
00:50:58,400 --> 00:51:00,040
- Me?
- Yes.

867
00:51:01,780 --> 00:51:04,100
It's cold.

868
00:51:04,100 --> 00:51:06,550
Cold? It's not cold.

869
00:51:06,550 --> 00:51:08,190
It's warm.

870
00:51:08,190 --> 00:51:10,240
I'm just saying.

871
00:51:10,240 --> 00:51:12,310
What is it?

872
00:51:13,590 --> 00:51:16,850
I was curious what you did yesterday.

873
00:51:16,850 --> 00:51:19,560
- Yesterday?
- We didn't see each other yesterday.

874
00:51:21,900 --> 00:51:24,710
I had a day with Jun Hyeon yesterday.

875
00:51:24,710 --> 00:51:25,850
Oh, you two...

876
00:51:25,850 --> 00:51:29,700
I haven't met up with Seong Min yet.
I think I will tomorrow.

877
00:51:29,700 --> 00:51:31,840
- Really?
- Yes.

878
00:51:33,980 --> 00:51:36,010
I think it will be tomorrow.

879
00:51:36,010 --> 00:51:38,520
- He is suddenly acting cute.
- He turned into a puppy.

880
00:51:38,520 --> 00:51:40,620
I thought you were free tomorrow.

881
00:51:40,620 --> 00:51:43,210
Tomorrow? I know.

882
00:51:47,640 --> 00:51:49,260
What about you?

883
00:51:49,260 --> 00:51:51,090
What about me?

884
00:51:51,090 --> 00:51:52,630
What did you do yesterday?

885
00:51:52,630 --> 00:51:55,640
- "I ended things with her."
- Yes, tell her.

886
00:51:56,560 --> 00:51:58,980
I went to Gangneung.

887
00:52:03,480 --> 00:52:06,290
It was almost evening when we arrived.

888
00:52:06,290 --> 00:52:08,100
It took almost four hours to get there.

889
00:52:08,100 --> 00:52:10,200
- Wow.
- Daebak.

890
00:52:10,200 --> 00:52:11,900
That's why I got back late.

891
00:52:11,900 --> 00:52:14,370
It took about three hours to get back.

892
00:52:15,490 --> 00:52:16,720
I see.

893
00:52:16,720 --> 00:52:18,990
You didn't drive on the way back, right?

894
00:52:18,990 --> 00:52:21,730
I came by myself. We came back separately.

895
00:52:21,730 --> 00:52:23,710
She knows now.

896
00:52:23,710 --> 00:52:25,820
Did you get some sleep on the way back?

897
00:52:25,820 --> 00:52:28,160
- I couldn't sleep.
- Why not?

898
00:52:30,320 --> 00:52:32,260
I just couldn't.

899
00:52:40,170 --> 00:52:41,410
I missed you.

900
00:52:41,410 --> 00:52:43,130
He missed her!

901
00:52:43,130 --> 00:52:45,280
This is crazy.

902
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:48,450
Really?

903
00:52:49,600 --> 00:52:51,370
You must know.

904
00:52:52,940 --> 00:52:56,620
- What do I know?
- How could she know?

905
00:52:57,660 --> 00:52:59,210
I'm sorry.

906
00:53:02,660 --> 00:53:05,590
- Don't be sorry.
- I didn't know, either.

907
00:53:07,870 --> 00:53:11,010
When we talked here in the morning,

908
00:53:11,010 --> 00:53:13,830
I felt heartbroken.

909
00:53:16,510 --> 00:53:19,490
I think I hurt your feelings.

910
00:53:19,490 --> 00:53:25,440
I think you got your feelings
heard out of the blue.

911
00:53:27,030 --> 00:53:29,870
When we had a date when you felt hurt,

912
00:53:29,870 --> 00:53:35,740
you treated me the same as usual.

913
00:53:35,740 --> 00:53:40,500
- I suddenly realized that.
- Right. At least he gets it.

914
00:53:40,500 --> 00:53:42,240
I wanted to tell you that.

915
00:53:42,240 --> 00:53:45,540
- It's melting her heart.
- Wu Yeol knows what to do.

916
00:53:45,540 --> 00:53:49,900
I invited you here because
I wanted to tell you that.

917
00:53:54,020 --> 00:53:56,400
Okay, thank you.

918
00:54:00,310 --> 00:54:02,460
Thank you for listening.

919
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:07,310
Are you done talking? Are you done?

920
00:54:07,310 --> 00:54:09,200
Yes, I feel better.

921
00:54:09,200 --> 00:54:10,900
Good job.

922
00:54:13,180 --> 00:54:18,560
You must've had a lot of worries
and thoughts.

923
00:54:27,150 --> 00:54:29,600
Do you know the rules for Yunnori?

924
00:54:34,000 --> 00:54:36,380
[Starting to play Yunnori]

925
00:54:36,380 --> 00:54:38,900
It's 4:4 like this.

926
00:54:38,900 --> 00:54:40,030
4:4 like this?

927
00:54:40,030 --> 00:54:42,880
We already won.
We won with our looks already.

928
00:54:42,880 --> 00:54:46,040
No, that's not what I meant!

929
00:54:46,040 --> 00:54:47,690
[Shocked]

930
00:54:48,360 --> 00:54:50,860
- Did you drink?
- That's not what I meant.

931
00:54:50,860 --> 00:54:53,090
I meant the expressions.

932
00:54:53,090 --> 00:54:54,900
- Confidence?
- Let's try again.

933
00:54:54,900 --> 00:54:56,930
What will our team do?

934
00:54:56,930 --> 00:55:00,720
The winning team will sit here,
and the losing team will bow.

935
00:55:00,720 --> 00:55:03,360
- Here I go.
- Fighting. Go.

936
00:55:03,360 --> 00:55:05,420
You're good.

937
00:55:05,420 --> 00:55:07,630
- It's a yut!
- He's good.

938
00:55:07,630 --> 00:55:09,000
He's good.

939
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:12,490
Hold on, don't touch it. Go again.

940
00:55:12,490 --> 00:55:14,190
Hurry up.

941
00:55:14,190 --> 00:55:15,480
Why are you so touchy?

942
00:55:15,480 --> 00:55:17,920
- No, no.
- Why so touchy?

943
00:55:17,920 --> 00:55:20,900
- Seo Won, try to relax.
- Make yourself at home.

944
00:55:20,900 --> 00:55:22,780
His posture is wrong to begin with.

945
00:55:22,780 --> 00:55:24,440
[Ready to spring out]

946
00:55:28,170 --> 00:55:29,260
[Min Ju got a geol]

947
00:55:29,260 --> 00:55:32,540
- Nice.
- A geol.

948
00:55:32,540 --> 00:55:33,830
With this?

949
00:55:33,830 --> 00:55:35,160
Go in right away.

950
00:55:36,030 --> 00:55:37,370
Smart!

951
00:55:37,370 --> 00:55:39,780
- Good job.
- Min Ju.

952
00:55:41,700 --> 00:55:42,860
[Handing over]

953
00:55:45,330 --> 00:55:49,230
I didn't feel so great yesterday.

954
00:55:50,250 --> 00:55:52,590
I was so tired during the date.

955
00:55:52,590 --> 00:55:54,140
So I got an IV treatment.

956
00:55:54,140 --> 00:55:55,810
- Really?
- Yes.

957
00:55:57,040 --> 00:55:58,600
[Jun Hyeon was with Yu Gyeong
while she was sick]

958
00:55:58,600 --> 00:56:00,780
Do we need a temperature check?
She checked in.

959
00:56:00,780 --> 00:56:02,490
Kang Yu Gyeong.

960
00:56:04,240 --> 00:56:07,460
Jun Hyeon waited for me the entire time.

961
00:56:14,090 --> 00:56:16,350
That doesn't count. That doesn't count.

962
00:56:16,350 --> 00:56:18,380
That doesn't count.

963
00:56:18,380 --> 00:56:22,330
He keeps giving her the sticks
whenever it's her turn.

964
00:56:22,330 --> 00:56:24,130
It doesn't count.

965
00:56:24,130 --> 00:56:27,140
[He keeps handing her the sticks
whenever it's her turn]

966
00:56:27,140 --> 00:56:29,280
- Look at him.
- What's the deal?

967
00:56:29,280 --> 00:56:30,920
Wu Yeol notices it.

968
00:56:30,920 --> 00:56:33,380
- Toss high, Yu Gyeong.
- It's over if it's a geol.

969
00:56:33,380 --> 00:56:35,460
It's over if it's a geol.

970
00:56:35,460 --> 00:56:38,120
[They win if Yu Gyeong gets a geol]

971
00:56:38,120 --> 00:56:41,140
- Wow.
- Geol. It's over.

972
00:56:41,140 --> 00:56:43,320
[The left team wins]

973
00:56:43,320 --> 00:56:44,690
It bothers him.

974
00:56:44,690 --> 00:56:45,920
[Bothered]

975
00:56:47,360 --> 00:56:50,360
- Did we win?
- It's daebak!

976
00:56:50,360 --> 00:56:53,020
Let's receive their bow first.

977
00:56:53,020 --> 00:56:55,900
Go ahead and bow your heads.

978
00:56:57,770 --> 00:57:00,250
[Clearing throat]

979
00:57:00,250 --> 00:57:03,740
Happy New Year.

980
00:57:03,740 --> 00:57:05,680
This feels so amazing. What's the deal?

981
00:57:05,680 --> 00:57:08,470
- So cute.
- Happy New Year.

982
00:57:08,470 --> 00:57:12,550
- You have anything for us?
- No, we don't.

983
00:57:12,550 --> 00:57:14,920
Here you go.

984
00:57:18,100 --> 00:57:19,840
That was fun.

985
00:57:20,710 --> 00:57:27,220
[The first Lunar New Year in the house]

986
00:57:28,310 --> 00:57:30,900
They're spending the Lunar New Year together.

987
00:57:32,900 --> 00:57:35,630
Wu Yeol is anxious now that
he knows the dynamics.

988
00:57:35,630 --> 00:57:39,280
Everything should bother him from now on.

989
00:57:39,280 --> 00:57:42,670
Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong high-fived
while playing Yunnori.

990
00:57:42,670 --> 00:57:44,610
He kept staring at them constantly.

991
00:57:44,610 --> 00:57:46,350
He wasn't exactly thrilled.

992
00:57:46,350 --> 00:57:48,050
He needs to know how that feels.

993
00:57:48,050 --> 00:57:50,510
Wu Yeol was surprised, as you mentioned.

994
00:57:50,510 --> 00:57:53,950
They finally hung out in the tea room,
but she was like, "I'm tired."

995
00:57:53,950 --> 00:57:57,950
He was like, "She used to be happy
whenever she was with me."

996
00:57:57,950 --> 00:57:59,510
She changed.

997
00:57:59,510 --> 00:58:01,370
She didn't interrogate him at all.

998
00:58:01,370 --> 00:58:03,810
She didn't say, "Why were you late?
What did you do?"

999
00:58:03,810 --> 00:58:07,120
But he just told her everything.

1000
00:58:07,120 --> 00:58:10,180
He struggles to say cheesy things.

1001
00:58:10,180 --> 00:58:12,090
I missed you.

1002
00:58:12,090 --> 00:58:13,950
"I missed you" was amazing.

1003
00:58:13,950 --> 00:58:16,550
That was a lot to express on his part.

1004
00:58:16,550 --> 00:58:19,860
Yu Gyeong takes the lead from now on, right?

1005
00:58:19,860 --> 00:58:23,200
Because Wu Yeol has basically decided.

1006
00:58:23,200 --> 00:58:26,130
But Yu Gyeong still has options.

1007
00:58:26,130 --> 00:58:27,970
She's choosing one out of three.

1008
00:58:27,970 --> 00:58:31,300
It was like that from the beginning
for Yu Gyeong.

1009
00:58:31,300 --> 00:58:34,100
[A warm afternoon]

1010
00:58:35,930 --> 00:58:37,960
A date with Seong Min.

1011
00:58:37,960 --> 00:58:41,160
[Yu Gyeong is waiting for Seong Min]

1012
00:58:42,640 --> 00:58:44,900
[Seong Min just left work]

1013
00:58:44,900 --> 00:58:46,770
He looks so cool.

1014
00:58:48,730 --> 00:58:50,630
[On his way to meet Yu Gyeong]

1015
00:58:53,260 --> 00:58:55,240
He's smiling.

1016
00:59:00,400 --> 00:59:03,020
- Come on, Oppa.
- What?

1017
00:59:03,020 --> 00:59:06,510
You shouldn't have
covered your face with this.

1018
00:59:06,510 --> 00:59:09,440
- I wanted to find you.
- Really?

1019
00:59:09,440 --> 00:59:12,420
- Have you had lunch?
- I ate at work.

1020
00:59:12,420 --> 00:59:15,110
It's late. It's evening now.

1021
00:59:16,270 --> 00:59:18,690
Wow, so pretty.

1022
00:59:18,690 --> 00:59:22,190
LP records. There are real LP records.

1023
00:59:22,190 --> 00:59:23,620
So nice.

1024
00:59:23,620 --> 00:59:27,690
[There is a wall of LPs here]

1025
00:59:27,690 --> 00:59:32,390
I can listen to my favorite song here.

1026
00:59:32,390 --> 00:59:34,520
I'll write down my favorite, too.

1027
00:59:35,870 --> 00:59:38,690
I have so many favorites.

1028
00:59:38,690 --> 00:59:42,510
[Writing down some of their favorites]

1029
00:59:42,510 --> 00:59:44,190
I'm excited.

1030
00:59:45,670 --> 00:59:49,450
[Yu Gyeong's request is being played]

1031
00:59:50,060 --> 00:59:51,880
This is my song.

1032
00:59:51,880 --> 00:59:54,760
I really love this song.

1033
00:59:56,450 --> 01:00:00,640
I used to listen to this song
without much thinking.

1034
01:00:00,640 --> 01:00:03,840
But I listened to it loudly
while driving once,

1035
01:00:03,840 --> 01:00:05,810
and I suddenly heard it.

1036
01:00:05,810 --> 01:00:09,140
- The lyrics?
- No, the song.

1037
01:00:09,140 --> 01:00:11,370
I used to just listen to it before.

1038
01:00:11,370 --> 01:00:13,080
So, I listen to it nonstop now.

1039
01:00:13,080 --> 01:00:16,470
Right, sometimes they suddenly click.

1040
01:00:19,930 --> 01:00:21,690
I love it.

1041
01:00:22,810 --> 01:00:24,660
His eyes are heart-shaped.

1042
01:00:29,890 --> 01:00:32,030
I like Hyukoh, too.

1043
01:00:34,300 --> 01:00:36,020
This is so good.

1044
01:00:36,990 --> 01:00:38,670
He keeps smiling.

1045
01:00:39,370 --> 01:00:44,130
I had this thought while going to work.

1046
01:00:44,130 --> 01:00:46,520
I just wanted us to...

1047
01:00:46,520 --> 01:00:50,900
rest without doing anything else today.

1048
01:00:50,900 --> 01:00:52,470
Maybe you seem tired.

1049
01:00:52,470 --> 01:00:55,180
- I think you seem tired.
- Really?

1050
01:00:55,180 --> 01:00:57,810
She looks very tired right now.

1051
01:00:57,810 --> 01:00:59,560
Thank you.

1052
01:01:00,650 --> 01:01:02,140
I also had this thought.

1053
01:01:02,140 --> 01:01:05,730
I asked you out on a date the next day.

1054
01:01:06,730 --> 01:01:12,030
I worried that I was stressing you
out by doing that.

1055
01:01:15,430 --> 01:01:18,280
But at the same time...

1056
01:01:18,280 --> 01:01:21,650
- It's not like I could do nothing.
- Right.

1057
01:01:21,650 --> 01:01:25,980
I didn't want to sit back,
but I didn't want to pressure you.

1058
01:01:26,790 --> 01:01:32,760
I was wondering how I should be behaving.

1059
01:01:33,990 --> 01:01:39,600
Instead of trying to do something grand,

1060
01:01:39,600 --> 01:01:44,940
I thought it'd be better
to make you feel comfortable.

1061
01:01:48,720 --> 01:01:50,190
But...

1062
01:01:53,630 --> 01:01:56,950
since we're living together,

1063
01:01:56,950 --> 01:02:02,420
and we know what each other
is doing all the time...

1064
01:02:04,320 --> 01:02:09,520
we all pretty much know how we feel.

1065
01:02:09,520 --> 01:02:14,660
So, I think it's weird
not to talk about that.

1066
01:02:14,660 --> 01:02:21,800
I think it's more considerate
to tell the person about it.

1067
01:02:21,800 --> 01:02:27,150
[More cautious since she knows
how heavy it could feel]

1068
01:02:27,900 --> 01:02:32,560
I don't know. Don't stress
about stressing me out.

1069
01:02:32,560 --> 01:02:34,460
Don't stress about stressing you out.

1070
01:02:34,460 --> 01:02:36,800
It could stress you out more.

1071
01:02:36,800 --> 01:02:40,410
Right. Yu Gyeong is good with words.

1072
01:02:43,250 --> 01:02:46,960
This could be pressure for you, but...

1073
01:02:46,960 --> 01:02:52,180
I didn't really know my feelings.

1074
01:02:52,180 --> 01:02:54,810
I thought I was very honest.

1075
01:02:54,810 --> 01:02:58,040
- Wait, this is... wait a minute.
- No way.

1076
01:02:58,040 --> 01:02:59,750
I didn't differentiate...

1077
01:03:00,850 --> 01:03:04,810
between liking someone as a person
and liking them romantically.

1078
01:03:05,690 --> 01:03:08,100
At this rate, he'll say this
to a stranger on the street.

1079
01:03:08,100 --> 01:03:09,530
Hey, look...

1080
01:03:09,530 --> 01:03:11,670
That must've been a shocker for him.

1081
01:03:11,670 --> 01:03:14,390
He discovered an amazing truth.

1082
01:03:14,390 --> 01:03:16,980
As if he had discovered
the heliocentric theory.

1083
01:03:19,290 --> 01:03:23,570
- I realized that a few days ago.
- A few days ago?

1084
01:03:24,750 --> 01:03:26,980
I really didn't know.

1085
01:03:26,980 --> 01:03:29,320
I didn't know that I didn't know.

1086
01:03:29,320 --> 01:03:31,990
You don't know what you don't know.

1087
01:03:32,983 --> 01:03:35,812
I realized
I was romantically interested in you.

1088
01:03:35,812 --> 01:03:37,690
Right.

1089
01:03:37,690 --> 01:03:42,480
- I didn't know.
- Really?

1090
01:03:42,480 --> 01:03:49,340
I need to think more to figure out if
I didn't know or I wanted to hide it.

1091
01:03:53,270 --> 01:04:00,320
But in a way, I've become more certain.

1092
01:04:02,230 --> 01:04:04,780
I should be by now.

1093
01:04:04,780 --> 01:04:07,010
I could be wrong, but...

1094
01:04:07,010 --> 01:04:10,300
while we're eating together
and spending time,

1095
01:04:12,940 --> 01:04:16,690
- I think it's been you for a long time.
- Really...

1096
01:04:16,690 --> 01:04:19,540
- Seong Min is being so genuine.
- He is.

1097
01:04:19,540 --> 01:04:21,940
[Seong Min is telling her
his genuine feelings]

1098
01:04:30,080 --> 01:04:31,780
I guess I've been...

1099
01:04:33,330 --> 01:04:36,060
thinking alone too much, and I'm too late.

1100
01:04:42,540 --> 01:04:45,870
[But Yu Gyeong doesn't respond]

1101
01:04:48,150 --> 01:04:49,710
You don't have to say anything.

1102
01:04:49,710 --> 01:04:52,370
You don't have to for 30 minutes. Really.

1103
01:04:52,370 --> 01:04:54,810
- Come on.
- I mean it.

1104
01:04:59,460 --> 01:05:01,480
Are you busy on either Thursday or Friday?

1105
01:05:01,480 --> 01:05:03,330
Thursday or Friday?

1106
01:05:03,330 --> 01:05:05,730
No, nothing.

1107
01:05:05,730 --> 01:05:08,400
Should we set up a date
for one of those days?

1108
01:05:08,400 --> 01:05:12,980
- Oh, my gosh...
- Okay, even if it's brief...

1109
01:05:17,370 --> 01:05:20,240
- Friday?
- But why?

1110
01:05:20,240 --> 01:05:21,670
Yeah.

1111
01:05:23,020 --> 01:05:26,180
- Brief.
- Brief?

1112
01:05:26,180 --> 01:05:28,540
What should we eat?

1113
01:05:28,540 --> 01:05:33,600
[She's feeling pressured about Friday]

1114
01:05:34,520 --> 01:05:36,370
- It's getting late...
- Let's go.

1115
01:05:36,370 --> 01:05:40,240
- I had fun.
- Yeah, I had fun.

1116
01:05:40,240 --> 01:05:44,860
My goodwill toward him as a person
is about to run out.

1117
01:05:44,860 --> 01:05:46,680
I think it will be this year's catchphrase.

1118
01:05:46,680 --> 01:05:50,470
- Eana, I really like you as a person.
- You're the best.

1119
01:05:50,470 --> 01:05:51,780
But why is he repeating that?

1120
01:05:51,780 --> 01:05:56,020
And he even said Yu Gyeong looked tired

1121
01:05:56,020 --> 01:06:00,510
and he said he wanted her to relax
and not stress her out.

1122
01:06:00,510 --> 01:06:02,590
But this can be stressful,

1123
01:06:02,590 --> 01:06:04,690
and he says he likes her romantically.

1124
01:06:04,690 --> 01:06:05,940
And he asks her out again.

1125
01:06:05,940 --> 01:06:09,360
"Should we pick a date? What should
we eat?" This is too...

1126
01:06:09,360 --> 01:06:12,560
He put all the pressure on her,
and he says she can relax for 30 minutes.

1127
01:06:12,560 --> 01:06:13,630
[Mic drop]

1128
01:06:13,630 --> 01:06:16,640
He asked her out again,
and she said one thing.

1129
01:06:16,640 --> 01:06:18,170
"Brief."

1130
01:06:18,170 --> 01:06:19,370
Brief.

1131
01:06:19,370 --> 01:06:23,610
As for Yu Gyeong, she constantly
feels bad for him.

1132
01:06:23,610 --> 01:06:26,390
- She's put in a spot.
- She can't accept his feelings

1133
01:06:26,390 --> 01:06:29,640
but he keeps dumping his feelings
on her so wholeheartedly.

1134
01:06:29,640 --> 01:06:32,150
She feels so bad.

1135
01:06:32,150 --> 01:06:35,030
No one's here. All the slippers are here.

1136
01:06:35,030 --> 01:06:38,060
- Hi, hi.
- Hi.

1137
01:06:38,060 --> 01:06:39,450
You guys are the only ones here?

1138
01:06:39,450 --> 01:06:41,020
The guys went to the convenience store.

1139
01:06:41,020 --> 01:06:42,420
Oh, the store.

1140
01:06:42,420 --> 01:06:44,670
Do you want some rice cake soup?

1141
01:06:44,670 --> 01:06:46,700
- What's this?
- They were serious.

1142
01:06:46,700 --> 01:06:48,770
[Looking]

1143
01:06:55,230 --> 01:06:57,950
Look, Yu Gyeong is having a hard time.

1144
01:06:58,770 --> 01:07:00,980
[Sigh]

1145
01:07:01,510 --> 01:07:03,160
[The men return with a bunch of snacks]

1146
01:07:03,160 --> 01:07:04,940
Thank you.

1147
01:07:04,940 --> 01:07:06,960
This is so good.

1148
01:07:06,960 --> 01:07:08,490
- I bought it.
- You bought it?

1149
01:07:08,490 --> 01:07:10,710
- Didn't I do a good job?
- Good job.

1150
01:07:10,710 --> 01:07:12,950
[Enjoying rice cake soup]

1151
01:07:12,950 --> 01:07:15,730
- You had a drink.
- You're slightly flushed.

1152
01:07:15,730 --> 01:07:19,040
Wu Yeol must be bothered by Seong Min, too.

1153
01:07:19,040 --> 01:07:20,770
Where did you go?

1154
01:07:20,770 --> 01:07:23,960
- We drank and went to a bar.
- Which bar?

1155
01:07:25,270 --> 01:07:26,690
[Cracking up]

1156
01:07:26,690 --> 01:07:29,150
- Why do you want to know where?
- You're asking too much.

1157
01:07:29,150 --> 01:07:31,870
- I'm curious.
- Which bar?

1158
01:07:31,870 --> 01:07:35,490
It was almost an interrogation. "Which bar?"

1159
01:07:35,490 --> 01:07:37,660
How much did you drink?

1160
01:07:40,560 --> 01:07:42,750
Seong Min is hyped up today.

1161
01:07:42,750 --> 01:07:47,110
- Gosh, Min Ju is struggling, too.
- Both of them are.

1162
01:07:52,620 --> 01:07:56,010
- Yu Gyeong, tell her. Say you're struggling.
- You have to.

1163
01:07:56,010 --> 01:07:59,910
- What?
- We don't have much time left.

1164
01:08:00,910 --> 01:08:04,400
I should follow my heart.

1165
01:08:04,400 --> 01:08:08,820
Not worry about others.
It's time for me to gather

1166
01:08:08,820 --> 01:08:10,350
my feelings that were once opened.

1167
01:08:10,350 --> 01:08:11,910
- That's right.
- You should have closure now.

1168
01:08:11,910 --> 01:08:14,580
Is that hard to do?

1169
01:08:14,580 --> 01:08:16,910
[Hesitating]

1170
01:08:16,910 --> 01:08:20,620
Seong Min wants to go out on a weekday.

1171
01:08:20,620 --> 01:08:23,740
- What day?
- Friday.

1172
01:08:23,740 --> 01:08:27,100
But I know he's doing his best.

1173
01:08:27,100 --> 01:08:31,020
Of course, I have the right to reject it, but

1174
01:08:31,020 --> 01:08:34,740
I feel like I shouldn't.

1175
01:08:34,740 --> 01:08:36,950
So, I said yes.

1176
01:08:41,840 --> 01:08:45,880
And I want to avoid it.

1177
01:08:45,880 --> 01:08:48,050
He asked to see you on Friday?

1178
01:08:48,050 --> 01:08:50,760
- She's saying she doesn't want to see him.
- Right.

1179
01:08:50,760 --> 01:08:52,720
After work?

1180
01:08:55,440 --> 01:09:00,550
And Wu Yeol could also wonder
what it's about.

1181
01:09:00,550 --> 01:09:02,380
I feel like
I shouldn't reject him altogether.

1182
01:09:02,380 --> 01:09:05,600
- Right, right.
- Women should talk about this.

1183
01:09:05,600 --> 01:09:09,180
I should talk to him seriously.

1184
01:09:09,180 --> 01:09:12,630
Tell him that
I want to focus on my feelings...

1185
01:09:14,490 --> 01:09:17,070
That's really awkward, too.

1186
01:09:18,260 --> 01:09:20,260
[Min Ju is feeling complicated]

1187
01:09:20,260 --> 01:09:24,730
This could bruise Min Ju's ego,
but Yu Gyeong has to.

1188
01:09:28,800 --> 01:09:32,190
Min Ju is having all kinds of mixed feelings.

1189
01:09:41,740 --> 01:09:45,920
Unni, I'll go out and see how things are.

1190
01:09:45,920 --> 01:09:50,930
[Yu Gyeong leaves the room]

1191
01:09:51,800 --> 01:09:54,640
[Closes eyes]

1192
01:10:13,860 --> 01:10:16,370
I've never seen her like this before.

1193
01:10:17,920 --> 01:10:27,040
[Finally, she starts crying]

1194
01:10:42,550 --> 01:10:47,650
[Once she started crying...]

1195
01:10:51,440 --> 01:10:57,940
[she cried for a long time]

1196
01:11:15,680 --> 01:11:18,890
- Oh, no!
- She's sobbing.

1197
01:11:19,680 --> 01:11:21,360
But I get where Yu Gyeong is coming from.

1198
01:11:21,360 --> 01:11:23,290
[Totally empathizing with her]

1199
01:11:23,290 --> 01:11:26,020
But that's making Min Ju cry
as she listened to her.

1200
01:11:26,020 --> 01:11:28,490
Min Ju could think,
"That's how he treats someone else.

1201
01:11:28,490 --> 01:11:31,640
How could he not even look at me?"

1202
01:11:31,640 --> 01:11:36,350
I think she felt bad for foolish Seong Min.

1203
01:11:36,350 --> 01:11:38,000
- Right.
- I think that's mixed in.

1204
01:11:38,000 --> 01:11:40,880
Honestly, Min Ju cried...

1205
01:11:40,880 --> 01:11:43,970
but I think those were good tears.

1206
01:11:43,970 --> 01:11:45,770
- She should come to her senses.
- She needs to.

1207
01:11:45,770 --> 01:11:48,530
She was sad and embarrassed.

1208
01:11:48,530 --> 01:11:51,550
She must've had all kinds of thoughts.

1209
01:11:58,260 --> 01:12:01,280
That's really good.

1210
01:12:02,080 --> 01:12:03,760
Hi.

1211
01:12:03,760 --> 01:12:05,810
- Why are you so red?
- What?

1212
01:12:05,810 --> 01:12:08,280
- Why are you so flushed?
- Really?

1213
01:12:08,280 --> 01:12:11,580
- Is there a seat?
- You're red as your lips.

1214
01:12:11,580 --> 01:12:13,440
Thanks.

1215
01:12:14,940 --> 01:12:15,970
[Sigh]

1216
01:12:15,970 --> 01:12:19,370
It's tough to cancel plans with your friends.

1217
01:12:25,990 --> 01:12:28,640
- What did you do?
- Just one thing?

1218
01:12:31,330 --> 01:12:33,070
[Mouthing something]

1219
01:12:35,410 --> 01:12:37,370
She's saying something to him.

1220
01:12:39,800 --> 01:12:42,690
Oh, no. Don't get too excited. Just go.

1221
01:12:50,930 --> 01:12:52,870
[Running up]

1222
01:12:54,730 --> 01:12:58,080
She's canceling the date
so cheerfully like that?

1223
01:12:59,200 --> 01:13:01,940
- Would you go to the tea room with me?
- Sure, sure.

1224
01:13:01,940 --> 01:13:05,200
Oh, no. His heart must be racing.

1225
01:13:06,070 --> 01:13:10,160
- You know how you asked to go out on Friday?
- She's getting to the point.

1226
01:13:10,160 --> 01:13:13,460
I've been thinking...

1227
01:13:13,460 --> 01:13:16,440
and we don't have much time left. So...

1228
01:13:16,440 --> 01:13:19,100
You don't, either, Yu Gyeong.

1229
01:13:20,130 --> 01:13:25,570
I thought I could hang out with you,

1230
01:13:25,570 --> 01:13:28,250
but on the flip side,

1231
01:13:28,250 --> 01:13:34,740
I think I should look
more closely into my heart.

1232
01:13:38,840 --> 01:13:44,570
So, I started wondering
if that's the right thing to do.

1233
01:13:44,570 --> 01:13:47,180
Now that I think about it.

1234
01:13:47,180 --> 01:13:48,980
So, I guess...

1235
01:13:51,360 --> 01:13:53,620
up until now...

1236
01:13:56,960 --> 01:14:01,520
if I thought of the other person,

1237
01:14:01,520 --> 01:14:07,830
I think I should think
about myself the most now.

1238
01:14:07,830 --> 01:14:09,700
- Good job, good job.
- Nice.

1239
01:14:09,700 --> 01:14:14,730
- Seong Min should get it.
- So, I wanted to tell you that.

1240
01:14:14,730 --> 01:14:18,460
Meeting you on Friday...

1241
01:14:18,460 --> 01:14:21,500
I don't think I'd feel good about it.

1242
01:14:21,500 --> 01:14:23,650
Good job, really.

1243
01:14:23,650 --> 01:14:25,020
[Head down]

1244
01:14:25,900 --> 01:14:27,660
Okay, okay.

1245
01:14:29,700 --> 01:14:33,580
I don't know. I just feel bad now.

1246
01:14:33,580 --> 01:14:36,100
No, whatever makes you feel better.

1247
01:14:37,190 --> 01:14:39,240
It's okay.

1248
01:14:39,240 --> 01:14:41,240
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

1249
01:14:43,260 --> 01:14:45,930
I just wonder...

1250
01:14:45,930 --> 01:14:48,190
if I could...

1251
01:14:48,190 --> 01:14:51,670
enjoy myself with you even then.

1252
01:14:51,670 --> 01:14:55,120
[Seong Min waits until Yu Gyeong finishes]

1253
01:14:55,120 --> 01:14:57,210
- Yeah.
- Sure.

1254
01:14:57,940 --> 01:15:00,320
That's how I feel.

1255
01:15:00,320 --> 01:15:02,480
I understand.

1256
01:15:05,370 --> 01:15:07,390
Thank you.

1257
01:15:07,390 --> 01:15:10,350
Is that why you called me so urgently?

1258
01:15:10,350 --> 01:15:11,810
I kept going...

1259
01:15:12,820 --> 01:15:15,280
It took her a lot of courage.

1260
01:15:15,280 --> 01:15:17,550
Thanks for hearing me out.

1261
01:15:17,550 --> 01:15:19,840
[Yu Gyeong gathered the courage
to reject him]

1262
01:15:19,840 --> 01:15:22,460
As Jun Hyeon said, this is the
time for them to be selfish.

1263
01:15:22,460 --> 01:15:24,040
- There's not much time.
- That's right.

1264
01:15:24,040 --> 01:15:29,090
A healthy rejection and the other
person accepting it are so crucial.

1265
01:15:29,090 --> 01:15:32,160
That must be difficult.

1266
01:15:32,160 --> 01:15:33,990
[Yu Gyeong returns to the first floor]

1267
01:15:38,810 --> 01:15:41,390
Where did everyone go?

1268
01:15:41,390 --> 01:15:43,060
She's sitting next to Wu Yeol.

1269
01:15:43,060 --> 01:15:44,990
- Do you like this?
- Yeah!

1270
01:15:44,990 --> 01:15:47,380
- He ate everything.
- I ate it all.

1271
01:15:47,380 --> 01:15:51,160
- Why are you so red?
- I'm drunk.

1272
01:15:51,160 --> 01:15:54,260
- Why are you so red?
- I'm drunk.

1273
01:15:55,270 --> 01:15:58,050
- You drunks.
- Why are you so red?

1274
01:15:58,050 --> 01:16:00,220
You were red when you came down.

1275
01:16:00,220 --> 01:16:01,140
Really?

1276
01:16:01,140 --> 01:16:04,930
- What did you drink today?
- Did something make you blush today?

1277
01:16:04,930 --> 01:16:08,520
- Did something make you blush?
- I'm feeling threatened.

1278
01:16:08,520 --> 01:16:09,720
I'm feeling threatened.

1279
01:16:09,720 --> 01:16:12,220
Wu Yeol and Jun Hyeon
are saying the same thing.

1280
01:16:12,220 --> 01:16:14,380
You weren't wearing earrings on our date.

1281
01:16:15,610 --> 01:16:18,980
What are you saying? What's up with you?

1282
01:16:18,980 --> 01:16:22,380
Do you want them? You want to wear them?

1283
01:16:29,390 --> 01:16:31,160
Did you fill the fridge?

1284
01:16:31,160 --> 01:16:33,370
Yeah, it's full to the brim.

1285
01:16:33,370 --> 01:16:34,990
O-Oppa... Oppa-

1286
01:16:34,990 --> 01:16:36,230
[Copies]

1287
01:16:36,230 --> 01:16:38,990
- The three of us went together.
- Seo Won, Hyung, and I went.

1288
01:16:38,990 --> 01:16:41,150
I cooked rice cake soup even though I won.

1289
01:16:42,150 --> 01:16:44,890
I won, but I made the rice cake soup.

1290
01:16:46,020 --> 01:16:47,970
- It's good, right?
- Why is it crispy?

1291
01:16:47,970 --> 01:16:49,930
- It's good, right?
- You didn't eat rice cake, huh?

1292
01:16:49,930 --> 01:16:51,950
No, I didn't get to.

1293
01:16:51,950 --> 01:16:53,270
[Glances]

1294
01:16:54,460 --> 01:16:56,050
You want milk?

1295
01:16:57,530 --> 01:16:59,040
With what cup?

1296
01:16:59,840 --> 01:17:01,410
I'll pour it here.

1297
01:17:02,520 --> 01:17:05,500
- I'll empty this for you.
-Thanks.

1298
01:17:09,930 --> 01:17:11,570
- You want more?
- Yeah.

1299
01:17:12,910 --> 01:17:14,350
Good.

1300
01:17:14,350 --> 01:17:17,290
- Sure.
- Thanks.

1301
01:17:22,730 --> 01:17:24,250
[Clumsy Min Ju joins]

1302
01:17:24,250 --> 01:17:27,390
- So annoying!
- What's wrong? What's wrong?

1303
01:17:27,390 --> 01:17:29,320
How sensitive can you be?

1304
01:17:29,320 --> 01:17:32,730
Min Ju, the details on your shirt
look so pretty.

1305
01:17:32,730 --> 01:17:35,090
- On the sleeves.
- This?

1306
01:17:35,090 --> 01:17:37,750
- You actually noticed that? Thanks.
- It's pretty.

1307
01:17:37,750 --> 01:17:39,420
Did you layer it, or did it come like that?

1308
01:17:39,420 --> 01:17:41,580
- I layered it.
- Great style.

1309
01:17:41,580 --> 01:17:44,010
Of course.

1310
01:17:44,010 --> 01:17:47,150
What did we do in school?
Didn't we do things like this?

1311
01:17:47,150 --> 01:17:49,850
Unni, you're pretty good! Can you do this?

1312
01:17:49,850 --> 01:17:51,590
I can't do that.

1313
01:17:51,590 --> 01:17:52,420
- What's that?
- What's that?

1314
01:17:52,420 --> 01:17:55,240
Drawing a circle
and a triangle simultaneously.

1315
01:17:55,240 --> 01:17:58,670
- I can't.
- What's so hard?

1316
01:17:58,670 --> 01:18:01,110
- Wait, do it again.
- Show us, again.

1317
01:18:01,110 --> 01:18:03,300
Never mind!

1318
01:18:03,300 --> 01:18:06,000
I'm drawing two triangles.

1319
01:18:06,000 --> 01:18:07,580
I can't do it.

1320
01:18:08,350 --> 01:18:11,560
- I wore white for the first time today.
- Oh, you're right.

1321
01:18:11,560 --> 01:18:13,730
Are those workout clothes?

1322
01:18:13,730 --> 01:18:15,210
No, just-

1323
01:18:15,210 --> 01:18:18,590
Sorry, it was just so out of the blue.

1324
01:18:19,380 --> 01:18:22,670
It's pretty. It looks good on you.

1325
01:18:22,670 --> 01:18:24,429
You said you wear long sleeves for workouts.

1326
01:18:24,429 --> 01:18:25,635
Jun Hyeon, Jun Hyeon...

1327
01:18:25,635 --> 01:18:28,520
I did today. I wore black.

1328
01:18:28,520 --> 01:18:31,330
- Shall we head in?
- Yes. We have work tomorrow.

1329
01:18:31,330 --> 01:18:33,920
Jun Hyeon, you should wear white, too.

1330
01:18:35,480 --> 01:18:37,570
There's a lot, huh?

1331
01:18:37,570 --> 01:18:39,610
There's a lot. Right now?

1332
01:18:43,910 --> 01:18:46,610
We have work tomorrow.

1333
01:18:48,170 --> 01:18:49,580
[And then there were two]

1334
01:18:49,580 --> 01:18:52,600
Seems like they waited to be alone.

1335
01:18:54,080 --> 01:18:57,010
- When are you going to sleep?
- You're right.

1336
01:18:57,010 --> 01:18:59,220
I don't know. Why?

1337
01:18:59,220 --> 01:19:01,310
- Why be so coy?
- What do you mean?

1338
01:19:01,310 --> 01:19:04,360
- He's bothered by her tone.
- What about you?

1339
01:19:05,850 --> 01:19:07,860
I don't know.

1340
01:19:09,840 --> 01:19:11,520
What did you do today?

1341
01:19:11,520 --> 01:19:13,420
What are they doing?

1342
01:19:13,420 --> 01:19:15,840
We went to an LP bar today.

1343
01:19:15,840 --> 01:19:17,230
Alone?

1344
01:19:17,230 --> 01:19:20,180
Did you do anything after working out?

1345
01:19:21,160 --> 01:19:23,260
I was bored.

1346
01:19:23,260 --> 01:19:25,860
Since someone was out on a date.

1347
01:19:25,860 --> 01:19:27,600
I was bored.

1348
01:19:28,410 --> 01:19:30,180
I had nothing to do.

1349
01:19:31,010 --> 01:19:34,560
[Returned from Gangneung early this morning]

1350
01:19:36,660 --> 01:19:41,840
[Wu Yeol lingered in the second-floor
living room for quite a while]

1351
01:19:44,810 --> 01:19:47,360
[Looks around]

1352
01:19:47,360 --> 01:19:49,460
I'm not sure if Yu Gyeong left.

1353
01:19:49,460 --> 01:19:50,980
She's not here.

1354
01:19:50,980 --> 01:19:54,960
[While Yu Gyeong wasn't around that day]

1355
01:19:58,210 --> 01:20:01,260
[Wu Yeol is in pajamas all day]

1356
01:20:04,420 --> 01:20:07,280
You even took a picture.

1357
01:20:07,280 --> 01:20:09,250
Big Guy?

1358
01:20:09,250 --> 01:20:10,400
This?

1359
01:20:10,400 --> 01:20:13,310
- Do you know what I'm talking about?
- Yeah.

1360
01:20:14,018 --> 01:20:15,791
The three of them hung out.

1361
01:20:15,791 --> 01:20:17,639
Wait, what's this?

1362
01:20:18,405 --> 01:20:21,880
- What's this?
- The three who worked out today.

1363
01:20:21,880 --> 01:20:23,350
Look!

1364
01:20:23,350 --> 01:20:25,910
Well, you know...

1365
01:20:25,910 --> 01:20:27,580
I didn't say anything.

1366
01:20:27,580 --> 01:20:29,790
It was their first time
taking pictures together.

1367
01:20:29,790 --> 01:20:32,290
I didn't tell them about us.

1368
01:20:32,290 --> 01:20:34,040
I'll pose like this.

1369
01:20:34,040 --> 01:20:35,850
[They took pictures together on their date]

1370
01:20:35,850 --> 01:20:38,770
- I like them.
- Me, too.

1371
01:20:38,770 --> 01:20:40,440
And...

1372
01:20:41,780 --> 01:20:42,740
[Close]

1373
01:20:42,740 --> 01:20:44,410
Gyu Ri wanted to...

1374
01:20:46,060 --> 01:20:49,140
take pictures,

1375
01:20:49,140 --> 01:20:53,180
but I rejected her and said
I'm taking them with Yu Gyeong.

1376
01:20:53,180 --> 01:20:55,320
For real.

1377
01:20:55,320 --> 01:20:58,320
- I'm serious.
- Oh, yeah?

1378
01:20:58,320 --> 01:21:00,510
That's understandable.

1379
01:21:00,510 --> 01:21:02,480
[LOL]

1380
01:21:02,480 --> 01:21:04,930
Wu Yeol, what's happened to you?

1381
01:21:04,930 --> 01:21:07,390
I was worried because you looked down today.

1382
01:21:07,390 --> 01:21:08,940
After returning today?

1383
01:21:08,940 --> 01:21:13,450
Did something happen,
or were you just feeling down?

1384
01:21:13,450 --> 01:21:15,250
That's not it.

1385
01:21:16,120 --> 01:21:19,980
I was thinking, "Why does Yu Gyeong

1386
01:21:19,980 --> 01:21:23,950
seem different than usual today?"

1387
01:21:23,950 --> 01:21:26,060
Even just now, with everyone.

1388
01:21:26,060 --> 01:21:28,840
That's why I kept glancing at you.

1389
01:21:28,840 --> 01:21:30,450
Oh, really? Just now?

1390
01:21:30,450 --> 01:21:31,870
She has a lot on her mind.

1391
01:21:31,870 --> 01:21:33,360
Did something happen?

1392
01:21:33,360 --> 01:21:36,940
I'm just walking on eggshells
around everyone.

1393
01:21:36,940 --> 01:21:41,120
That's only natural. You're Miss Popular.

1394
01:21:41,120 --> 01:21:43,340
You were aware?

1395
01:21:45,240 --> 01:21:46,920
Forgive me.

1396
01:21:46,920 --> 01:21:48,480
[Cracking up]

1397
01:21:48,480 --> 01:21:51,000
"You were aware,
and you still acted like that?"

1398
01:21:51,000 --> 01:21:53,170
You were aware, and you still did that?

1399
01:21:53,910 --> 01:21:56,540
[Shakes]

1400
01:21:58,220 --> 01:22:03,020
- I'm kidding.
- Now, you're the Yu Gyeong I know.

1401
01:22:03,020 --> 01:22:07,750
[Another night passes]

1402
01:22:07,750 --> 01:22:10,240
- How nice.
- This is so nice.

1403
01:22:10,240 --> 01:22:12,690
"You were aware, and you still did that?"

1404
01:22:12,690 --> 01:22:14,420
"You knew I'm Miss Popular,
yet you still did that?"

1405
01:22:14,420 --> 01:22:15,760
And when he went...

1406
01:22:15,760 --> 01:22:18,330
[Wu Yeol's whisper that made
everyone's hearts flutter]

1407
01:22:18,330 --> 01:22:20,560
- "Praise me!"
- "I did well, right?"

1408
01:22:20,560 --> 01:22:23,070
"Gyu Ri asked to take
pictures together, but I didn't."

1409
01:22:23,070 --> 01:22:25,560
I could almost see his tail
wagging like a propeller.

1410
01:22:25,560 --> 01:22:28,670
But she just nonchalantly responded,
"Good job."

1411
01:22:28,670 --> 01:22:29,700
Very casually.

1412
01:22:29,700 --> 01:22:33,610
That night, all tenants were
asked the same question.

1413
01:22:33,610 --> 01:22:37,550
Who's the person who has changed
you the most in Signal House?

1414
01:22:37,550 --> 01:22:41,390
As a result, those who were matched
with the person they chose

1415
01:22:41,390 --> 01:22:42,860
got to go on a date.

1416
01:22:42,860 --> 01:22:45,030
I wonder which couples successfully matched?

1417
01:22:45,030 --> 01:22:48,010
Let's watch the first couple's date.

1418
01:22:48,010 --> 01:22:51,960
We have no idea who matched with whom.

1419
01:22:51,960 --> 01:22:57,950
[Jun Hyeon waits for someone]

1420
01:22:57,950 --> 01:22:59,920
It's Jun Hyeon.

1421
01:23:03,630 --> 01:23:05,780
Oh? Those legs!

1422
01:23:05,780 --> 01:23:07,430
No way.

1423
01:23:10,720 --> 01:23:14,280
[Last night]

1424
01:23:14,280 --> 01:23:18,090
"The person who changed you the most?"

1425
01:23:19,900 --> 01:23:22,740
The person who changed me the most...

1426
01:23:22,740 --> 01:23:28,150
She saw me for who I am and
enabled me to be more honest.

1427
01:23:28,150 --> 01:23:29,340
Definitely Yu Gyeong.

1428
01:23:29,340 --> 01:23:34,910
I think he enabled me to express
my feelings wholeheartedly.

1429
01:23:34,910 --> 01:23:37,220
I felt she was a great person.

1430
01:23:37,220 --> 01:23:40,200
I realized we could click
regardless of our age difference.

1431
01:23:40,200 --> 01:23:41,950
The more time we spent together,

1432
01:23:41,950 --> 01:23:44,580
I discovered a better version of myself.

1433
01:23:44,580 --> 01:23:46,690
And I found myself laughing more.

1434
01:23:46,690 --> 01:23:50,350
It was a whole new feeling to know

1435
01:23:50,350 --> 01:23:54,010
I could be treated this way.

1436
01:23:54,010 --> 01:23:55,880
In that regard...

1437
01:23:55,880 --> 01:23:57,970
[The person who changed Yu Gyeong the most]

1438
01:23:57,970 --> 01:24:00,930
I think it's Jun Hyeon.

1439
01:24:00,930 --> 01:24:04,290
- No wonder!
- Jun Hyeon means more to her than expected.

1440
01:24:08,970 --> 01:24:11,480
That's crazy!

1441
01:24:15,200 --> 01:24:17,270
- Imagine how happy Jun Hyeon is.
- He must be so happy.

1442
01:24:17,270 --> 01:24:21,130
- Jun Hyeon always seems to end up lucky.
- Right?

1443
01:24:22,010 --> 01:24:23,570
Oppa...

1444
01:24:24,560 --> 01:24:27,180
- What's this?
- What do you think? It's Yu Gyeong.

1445
01:24:27,180 --> 01:24:28,960
What are you doing there?

1446
01:24:28,960 --> 01:24:31,050
It's cold!

1447
01:24:31,050 --> 01:24:34,250
- Her entrance is making my heart race!
- Are you cold?

1448
01:24:34,250 --> 01:24:35,560
So beautiful!

1449
01:24:35,560 --> 01:24:37,710
- You were sitting here?
- Yeah.

1450
01:24:37,710 --> 01:24:39,080
I was looking at the river.

1451
01:24:39,080 --> 01:24:41,980
I love Yu Gyeong and Jun Hyeon together.

1452
01:24:45,580 --> 01:24:48,290
They can go on a date only if they match.

1453
01:24:48,290 --> 01:24:49,540
Like destiny.

1454
01:24:49,540 --> 01:24:52,420
- We chose each other, apparently.
- We chose each other.

1455
01:24:53,360 --> 01:24:54,990
I wonder why.

1456
01:24:56,000 --> 01:24:58,290
I did choose you.

1457
01:24:58,290 --> 01:24:59,340
Me, too.

1458
01:24:59,340 --> 01:25:02,220
We chose each other.

1459
01:25:02,220 --> 01:25:03,230
It's like a movie.

1460
01:25:03,230 --> 01:25:07,750
Every time I dress up, I end up meeting you.

1461
01:25:07,750 --> 01:25:08,590
Exactly.

1462
01:25:08,590 --> 01:25:11,990
- I went totally formal today.
- We meet when you're formal.

1463
01:25:11,990 --> 01:25:15,290
How nice,
sitting here on a weekday afternoon.

1464
01:25:15,290 --> 01:25:18,360
- What about work?
- I threw in the towel and just came.

1465
01:25:18,360 --> 01:25:21,440
- Really?
- Jun Hyeon's way of talking cracks me up.

1466
01:25:21,440 --> 01:25:25,130
- It's practically the ocean.
- Seriously.

1467
01:25:25,130 --> 01:25:29,050
- How nice. The weather is really warm today.
- It's warm.

1468
01:25:32,350 --> 01:25:34,010
Thank you.

1469
01:25:34,010 --> 01:25:35,970
Open the car door. Treat her well.

1470
01:25:35,970 --> 01:25:37,540
Pitter-patter.

1471
01:25:37,540 --> 01:25:39,350
How are you feeling?

1472
01:25:39,350 --> 01:25:40,950
Good.

1473
01:25:40,950 --> 01:25:43,270
Powered by an IV drip.

1474
01:25:44,060 --> 01:25:46,320
The price of being date-obsessed.

1475
01:25:47,780 --> 01:25:50,550
- Exhaustion can't be helped.
- I paid the price.

1476
01:25:52,840 --> 01:25:56,800
I was just waiting there with
no idea who would show up.

1477
01:25:56,800 --> 01:26:00,000
So a genuine smile slipped out of me.

1478
01:26:00,000 --> 01:26:03,730
- You smiled?
- When you appeared from afar.

1479
01:26:03,730 --> 01:26:09,060
When you suddenly appeared as
I was sitting there, I couldn't help it.

1480
01:26:09,060 --> 01:26:10,360
[Can't hide his smile]

1481
01:26:10,360 --> 01:26:12,900
- What's this?
- Look at his smile.

1482
01:26:12,900 --> 01:26:14,040
I couldn't help but smile.

1483
01:26:14,040 --> 01:26:15,250
- You were glad to see me?
- I was.

1484
01:26:15,250 --> 01:26:18,940
Instead of feeling conflicted
about this situation,

1485
01:26:18,940 --> 01:26:20,560
they even make us feel happy.

1486
01:26:20,560 --> 01:26:25,160
Yeah. I was also really nervous about today.

1487
01:26:26,240 --> 01:26:29,200
- I honestly didn't see it coming.
- Really?

1488
01:26:29,200 --> 01:26:35,670
- Of course, he didn't.
- I had a feeling I'd meet you.

1489
01:26:35,670 --> 01:26:37,510
I thought a lot about it.

1490
01:26:37,510 --> 01:26:40,170
Yu Gyeong's feelings seem pretty deep.

1491
01:26:40,170 --> 01:26:45,580
When I think deeply about
who changed me the most,

1492
01:26:45,580 --> 01:26:47,730
I'm fully myself when I'm with you,

1493
01:26:47,730 --> 01:26:52,050
but there were also new sides
of me I didn't know existed.

1494
01:26:52,050 --> 01:26:54,880
Discovering a new side of yourself
is an incredible feeling.

1495
01:26:54,880 --> 01:27:01,170
I'm quick to size someone up
and make up my mind.

1496
01:27:01,170 --> 01:27:03,070
I make judgments about them.

1497
01:27:03,070 --> 01:27:07,110
What type of person they are?
About your compatibility?

1498
01:27:07,110 --> 01:27:12,700
I was full of bias against you at first.

1499
01:27:12,700 --> 01:27:14,670
You were engulfed by it, huh?

1500
01:27:15,640 --> 01:27:19,680
- "Gosh, he looks..."
- He looks too tough.

1501
01:27:19,680 --> 01:27:22,501
You thought I looked rough around the edges.

1502
01:27:22,501 --> 01:27:24,920
"He won't do."

1503
01:27:24,920 --> 01:27:28,950
When I learned about our age gap
and your job,

1504
01:27:28,950 --> 01:27:33,080
- I thought we were worlds apart.
- Worlds apart.

1505
01:27:33,080 --> 01:27:38,550
And I thought you would feel the same.

1506
01:27:38,550 --> 01:27:40,950
But the more we talked,

1507
01:27:40,950 --> 01:27:44,210
those prejudices faded away.
It was fascinating.

1508
01:27:44,210 --> 01:27:46,290
She must want to get to know him more.

1509
01:27:46,290 --> 01:27:50,800
So, it feels like you broke down
all of my prejudices.

1510
01:27:52,090 --> 01:27:56,080
Your blind dates must get rejected
at the front door then.

1511
01:27:57,280 --> 01:27:59,600
"I forgot I had plans."

1512
01:27:59,600 --> 01:28:02,990
- "Something suddenly came up."
- She comes off as cold at first.

1513
01:28:02,990 --> 01:28:04,130
She surprised you, though.

1514
01:28:04,130 --> 01:28:08,260
I didn't think I could break
through those prejudices.

1515
01:28:08,260 --> 01:28:09,740
I felt the prejudice.

1516
01:28:09,740 --> 01:28:12,800
Oh, really? For real?

1517
01:28:12,800 --> 01:28:18,350
So, I was going to hold a grudge
and tell you at the end.

1518
01:28:18,350 --> 01:28:20,760
"You have no judge of character."

1519
01:28:21,760 --> 01:28:24,120
- "You're the only one who doesn't know."
- He's so funny!

1520
01:28:24,120 --> 01:28:27,250
- To me? What the heck?
- I'm kidding.

1521
01:28:27,250 --> 01:28:31,330
I have a good judge of character.

1522
01:28:31,330 --> 01:28:33,650
Don't I?

1523
01:28:34,540 --> 01:28:38,910
Actually, this might also be a prejudice.

1524
01:28:38,910 --> 01:28:45,730
I found myself thinking, "This is the
type of person I like."

1525
01:28:45,730 --> 01:28:47,390
The more we talked.

1526
01:28:47,390 --> 01:28:53,800
I realized I can feel this way about
someone despite the huge age gap.

1527
01:28:53,800 --> 01:28:56,220
That's a wonderful thing to say.

1528
01:28:56,220 --> 01:29:02,460
I feel like I talk a lot about myself
when I'm with you.

1529
01:29:02,460 --> 01:29:03,920
That's right.

1530
01:29:03,920 --> 01:29:09,700
We must have a lot in common. That's crazy.

1531
01:29:09,700 --> 01:29:13,480
- This is nice.
- It's heartwarming.

1532
01:29:17,840 --> 01:29:22,520
[Paju Concino Concrete: Music Listening Room]

1533
01:29:23,670 --> 01:29:28,560
[An eye-catching wall of countless
speakers and records]

1534
01:29:31,500 --> 01:29:33,470
This is so nice.

1535
01:29:34,820 --> 01:29:37,540
- This is amazing.
- I know.

1536
01:29:39,120 --> 01:29:41,710
- It's captivating.
- It is.

1537
01:29:41,710 --> 01:29:43,760
[A place to lose yourself
in the space and the music]

1538
01:29:44,450 --> 01:29:47,680
- Do you like it?
- It's incredible.

1539
01:29:49,930 --> 01:29:53,870
When you took me to watch the musical...

1540
01:29:53,870 --> 01:29:56,500
When you took me to watch the musical...

1541
01:29:56,500 --> 01:29:58,690
Did she lean into him?

1542
01:29:58,690 --> 01:30:03,310
It felt like you put a lot
of thought into our dates.

1543
01:30:03,310 --> 01:30:06,610
- Of course, I did.
- I really enjoyed everything.

1544
01:30:08,460 --> 01:30:10,660
Can I look forward to more of this?

1545
01:30:10,660 --> 01:30:12,780
You can.

1546
01:30:14,550 --> 01:30:18,400
It seems like Yu Gyeong is
finally stepping on the gas.

1547
01:30:18,400 --> 01:30:21,770
It's not easy to feel

1548
01:30:21,770 --> 01:30:26,410
at ease or secure after coming to this place.

1549
01:30:26,410 --> 01:30:27,960
Right.

1550
01:30:27,960 --> 01:30:32,180
But I do feel that often. It's odd.

1551
01:30:32,180 --> 01:30:35,090
- When you're with me?
- Yeah.

1552
01:30:35,090 --> 01:30:37,140
Is this happening?

1553
01:30:37,140 --> 01:30:41,150
That's good. But I felt less comfortable
when I was with you.

1554
01:30:41,150 --> 01:30:42,190
- Really?
- That's true.

1555
01:30:42,190 --> 01:30:44,080
I do feel it.

1556
01:30:44,080 --> 01:30:47,400
I thought you felt the same.

1557
01:30:47,400 --> 01:30:51,180
This is how I feel when I'm with you.

1558
01:30:51,180 --> 01:30:55,840
When I'm with this person,
I become this type of person.

1559
01:30:55,840 --> 01:30:58,920
When I'm with that person,
I feel these emotions.

1560
01:30:58,920 --> 01:31:01,080
I'm able to sort everything out.

1561
01:31:01,080 --> 01:31:03,570
But when I'm with you,

1562
01:31:05,140 --> 01:31:10,270
I can't settle myself into one character.

1563
01:31:10,270 --> 01:31:13,290
- There are multiple sides to you?
- Yeah.

1564
01:31:13,290 --> 01:31:17,940
I feel comfortable at times, but then I feel

1565
01:31:18,960 --> 01:31:22,650
some level of tension.

1566
01:31:22,650 --> 01:31:24,810
- She must feel nervous.
- Exactly.

1567
01:31:24,810 --> 01:31:31,590
That's why it feels effortless yet
brand-new at the same time.

1568
01:31:32,530 --> 01:31:35,020
Jun Hyeon maintains
a great poker face, though.

1569
01:31:35,020 --> 01:31:38,870
- He must want to get up and tap dance.
- But he's staying calm.

1570
01:31:40,404 --> 01:31:42,960
To be honest,
what left the biggest impression

1571
01:31:42,960 --> 01:31:47,310
is when you opened the car door for me.

1572
01:31:47,310 --> 01:31:50,930
- Thank you.
- That must have left an impression.

1573
01:31:50,930 --> 01:31:53,910
- Thank you.
- It has to come naturally.

1574
01:31:53,910 --> 01:31:56,710
It must be a habit of Jun Hyeon's.

1575
01:31:57,840 --> 01:32:00,310
No one has done that for me before.

1576
01:32:00,310 --> 01:32:03,900
- It's nothing difficult.
- His response is cool.

1577
01:32:03,900 --> 01:32:07,760
At first, I thought, "Why is he doing this?"

1578
01:32:07,760 --> 01:32:10,160
"That's so cheesy."

1579
01:32:10,970 --> 01:32:15,260
Not to that point. But it was
just a new experience.

1580
01:32:15,260 --> 01:32:17,210
I'm thankful.

1581
01:32:17,210 --> 01:32:20,960
I also used to think that was cheesy.

1582
01:32:20,960 --> 01:32:24,080
- They're so affectionate.
- What I'm saying is...

1583
01:32:24,080 --> 01:32:30,680
Is it truly romance unless
there is some extravagance?

1584
01:32:30,680 --> 01:32:32,360
- It's not romance without extravagance.
- This is crazy.

1585
01:32:32,360 --> 01:32:35,540
- Game over.
- He nailed it!

1586
01:32:35,540 --> 01:32:37,257
This is the perfect spot to watch the sunset.

1587
01:32:37,257 --> 01:32:38,480
Exactly.

1588
01:32:38,480 --> 01:32:41,280
- The colors are more vibrant.
- At last, the sunset.

1589
01:32:41,280 --> 01:32:44,070
This might be our best date spot yet.

1590
01:32:44,070 --> 01:32:45,970
- Really?
- Yeah.

1591
01:32:45,970 --> 01:32:49,240
What else did we enjoy?

1592
01:32:49,240 --> 01:32:51,720
You said you enjoyed the movie.

1593
01:32:51,720 --> 01:32:53,910
Oh, the movie with Wu Yeol?

1594
01:32:53,910 --> 01:32:58,640
- Why, all of a sudden...
- I haven't had a change of heart.

1595
01:32:58,640 --> 01:33:03,580
But that was a blow to my mental state.

1596
01:33:03,580 --> 01:33:05,500
When I talked about it?

1597
01:33:05,500 --> 01:33:08,540
No, just your behavior.

1598
01:33:08,540 --> 01:33:12,830
"Behavior"? What can we do
about his word choice?

1599
01:33:12,830 --> 01:33:15,410
Your behavior was a big blow.

1600
01:33:15,410 --> 01:33:17,220
It's necessary to display some jealousy.

1601
01:33:17,220 --> 01:33:19,590
- To be honest, I was sulking about it.
- Oh, really?

1602
01:33:19,590 --> 01:33:22,850
At the time. But now I understand.

1603
01:33:22,850 --> 01:33:24,160
This is a necessary conversation.

1604
01:33:24,160 --> 01:33:30,220
But then you say it was the most
memorable moment during the truth game?

1605
01:33:30,220 --> 01:33:32,330
That's right.

1606
01:33:32,330 --> 01:33:37,470
There was probably a day we went
on a date, and I didn't text you.

1607
01:33:37,470 --> 01:33:40,600
- It's that day.
- The day of the truth game, I think.

1608
01:33:41,590 --> 01:33:44,740
- You're right!
- I was sulking that day, too.

1609
01:33:45,700 --> 01:33:49,540
- You're right. You didn't text me.
- "This won't work out."

1610
01:33:49,540 --> 01:33:52,510
- Really?
- "This is a really big blow."

1611
01:33:55,030 --> 01:33:58,730
- I'm just saying.
- This all probably comes off as charming.

1612
01:33:58,730 --> 01:34:01,810
I didn't know. I had no idea.

1613
01:34:03,220 --> 01:34:06,540
We only have a few days left.

1614
01:34:09,160 --> 01:34:12,320
I'm not sure what my true feelings are.

1615
01:34:16,800 --> 01:34:19,120
She must be confused.

1616
01:34:20,300 --> 01:34:22,770
- Let's eat dinner.
- Really?

1617
01:34:22,770 --> 01:34:25,050
I'm famished.

1618
01:34:25,050 --> 01:34:28,050
Let's finish listening to this. It's upbeat.

1619
01:34:28,850 --> 01:34:31,350
I could dance to this.

1620
01:34:31,350 --> 01:34:38,670
[Dusky evening]

1621
01:34:39,780 --> 01:34:41,770
Who could it be?

1622
01:34:41,770 --> 01:34:42,950
[Min Ju stands in an alleyway]

1623
01:34:42,950 --> 01:34:45,290
- Oh, it's Min Ju!
- It is Min Ju.

1624
01:34:46,240 --> 01:34:48,600
She cried so much.

1625
01:34:49,720 --> 01:34:53,570
[Who is Min Ju waiting for?]

1626
01:34:53,570 --> 01:34:56,000
Something's different about Min Ju.

1627
01:35:04,330 --> 01:35:06,150
It's Seong Min.

1628
01:35:08,580 --> 01:35:11,870
- What's going on?
- I can tell it's Min Ju even from behind.

1629
01:35:13,280 --> 01:35:14,830
She saw him and didn't smile.

1630
01:35:14,830 --> 01:35:16,950
- Where are you coming from? Work?
- Yeah.

1631
01:35:16,950 --> 01:35:19,300
She's very unfazed.

1632
01:35:19,300 --> 01:35:20,520
Did you see it just now?

1633
01:35:20,520 --> 01:35:22,530
- See what?
- The text.

1634
01:35:22,530 --> 01:35:24,320
- I didn't.
- We got a text from Signal.

1635
01:35:24,320 --> 01:35:25,670
Really?

1636
01:35:27,900 --> 01:35:33,440
["The person who changed me the most"]

1637
01:35:33,440 --> 01:35:34,610
[They chose each other]

1638
01:35:34,610 --> 01:35:36,010
- Each other?
- Yeah.

1639
01:35:36,010 --> 01:35:38,870
- Didn't you expect me?
- I did.

1640
01:35:38,870 --> 01:35:39,720
I did.

1641
01:35:39,720 --> 01:35:43,290
- But the vibe is a bit off.
- Since we constantly talked about it.

1642
01:35:43,290 --> 01:35:45,200
How we changed each other.

1643
01:35:45,200 --> 01:35:48,170
Min Ju's not in a good mood.

1644
01:35:48,170 --> 01:35:50,030
I was expecting you.

1645
01:35:51,480 --> 01:35:54,010
She can't keep smiling forever.

1646
01:35:54,010 --> 01:35:57,380
- When did you get off work?
- 8 p.m.

1647
01:35:57,380 --> 01:35:59,370
I think it's here.

1648
01:36:04,110 --> 01:36:08,210
[Furniture showroom in Gangnam-gu,
Nonhyeon-dong]

1649
01:36:09,250 --> 01:36:11,480
Wow, I feel right at home.

1650
01:36:11,480 --> 01:36:14,880
- You're right. I feel right at home.
- Right at home.

1651
01:36:15,680 --> 01:36:17,980
- We have this at home!
- This is ours!

1652
01:36:17,980 --> 01:36:20,500
I think we have this.

1653
01:36:20,500 --> 01:36:22,190
It's nice.

1654
01:36:23,670 --> 01:36:25,640
It smells good.

1655
01:36:25,640 --> 01:36:29,830
- It smells like home.
- Right. You're right.

1656
01:36:29,830 --> 01:36:33,230
- Our second floor living room.
- Dubai Chocolate Cookies.

1657
01:36:33,230 --> 01:36:37,350
- I always spin this while talking.
- Yeah. Me, too.

1658
01:36:38,420 --> 01:36:41,210
- Should we head to the third floor?
- Sure.

1659
01:36:42,170 --> 01:36:44,380
[Tea room in the showroom]

1660
01:36:44,890 --> 01:36:47,370
The atmosphere is so nice.

1661
01:36:48,470 --> 01:36:52,450
- It's so pretty.
- I love the atmosphere.

1662
01:36:52,450 --> 01:36:54,280
- Let's eat.
- Shall we?

1663
01:37:09,270 --> 01:37:10,810
It's good, right?

1664
01:37:12,120 --> 01:37:14,110
This is cool.

1665
01:37:14,110 --> 01:37:16,940
I've never tried most of these before.

1666
01:37:16,940 --> 01:37:20,220
[The serene atmosphere that calms the mind]

1667
01:37:20,990 --> 01:37:25,990
It's so serene here, right? It's so calming.

1668
01:37:29,830 --> 01:37:30,770
[Sighs]

1669
01:37:32,130 --> 01:37:37,400
Even if we hadn't matched,
we'd still have met, right?

1670
01:37:38,240 --> 01:37:40,160
Probably.

1671
01:37:40,160 --> 01:37:43,040
How did we end up matching?

1672
01:37:43,040 --> 01:37:48,640
I was kind of like,
"There's no looking back."

1673
01:37:48,640 --> 01:37:52,040
His answer to this question was Min Ju.

1674
01:37:56,560 --> 01:37:58,110
That's how it was.

1675
01:37:59,180 --> 01:38:01,240
Seong Min is getting the vibes.

1676
01:38:01,240 --> 01:38:05,330
- Min Ju has never been like that.
- Of course.

1677
01:38:09,580 --> 01:38:12,420
- Are you tired? You seem low-energy.
- Me?

1678
01:38:12,420 --> 01:38:14,430
I'm not tired.

1679
01:38:15,760 --> 01:38:17,900
- I'm not tired.
- You're not tired?

1680
01:38:23,160 --> 01:38:25,110
Are you emotionally drained?

1681
01:38:25,110 --> 01:38:28,160
- Is it that?
- What, while I've been here?

1682
01:38:28,160 --> 01:38:30,990
Because when I met you earlier...

1683
01:38:30,990 --> 01:38:35,660
you looked so tired and exhausted to me.

1684
01:38:37,240 --> 01:38:39,280
I am a bit exhausted.

1685
01:38:39,280 --> 01:38:42,400
- She is exhausted emotionally.
- Right.

1686
01:38:42,400 --> 01:38:48,900
But since we've had good food, I feel better.

1687
01:38:48,900 --> 01:38:51,780
- Want more?
- Why?

1688
01:38:51,780 --> 01:38:54,330
- You seem to like it.
- No, it's yours.

1689
01:38:56,530 --> 01:38:58,800
- This is enough.
- Yeah?

1690
01:39:01,740 --> 01:39:03,800
Are we eating too much?

1691
01:39:08,230 --> 01:39:12,290
- Gosh, Min Ju is not into it.
- That's not Min Ju's vibe right now.

1692
01:39:12,290 --> 01:39:14,340
[Glancing]

1693
01:39:14,340 --> 01:39:15,790
He's trying to read her.

1694
01:39:15,790 --> 01:39:19,310
Min Ju has always pretended to be okay.

1695
01:39:20,370 --> 01:39:27,880
[Min Ju does not seem like her usual self]

1696
01:39:34,940 --> 01:39:36,790
Goodness...

1697
01:39:41,800 --> 01:39:46,000
What's the hardest thing for you right now?

1698
01:39:46,000 --> 01:39:48,020
Here?

1699
01:39:49,570 --> 01:39:54,540
During my time in Signal House...

1700
01:39:55,700 --> 01:39:57,800
Min Ju doesn't know
how to express her feelings.

1701
01:39:57,800 --> 01:40:00,230
It's hard to put it into a sentence.

1702
01:40:00,230 --> 01:40:05,720
I know everyone's had hard
moments, all eight of us.

1703
01:40:05,720 --> 01:40:13,490
I've been trying to fight
and overcome them, but...

1704
01:40:14,980 --> 01:40:18,630
I think they piled up and exploded.

1705
01:40:18,630 --> 01:40:23,790
The things that made me sad,
that I struggled with.

1706
01:40:23,790 --> 01:40:25,920
The things that bothered me.

1707
01:40:25,920 --> 01:40:31,670
I think they all came out.

1708
01:40:31,670 --> 01:40:34,710
It's a good thing they all came out.

1709
01:40:34,710 --> 01:40:36,250
Yesterday?

1710
01:40:46,950 --> 01:40:53,210
You know what you said
in the restaurant in Namyangju?

1711
01:40:53,210 --> 01:40:56,390
Hearing those things...

1712
01:40:56,390 --> 01:40:59,950
They did come as a surprise to me.

1713
01:40:59,950 --> 01:41:08,370
But I was already a little aware...

1714
01:41:08,370 --> 01:41:15,110
I wasn't, but I tried to be stoic about it,
at least on the outside.

1715
01:41:15,110 --> 01:41:21,270
I was able to get through it. I understood.

1716
01:41:23,630 --> 01:41:27,960
But while we were on a walk, you said

1717
01:41:27,960 --> 01:41:33,210
"After I told you that yesterday,
I feel much more at ease."

1718
01:41:33,210 --> 01:41:36,220
That was such a shock.

1719
01:41:40,080 --> 01:41:44,510
All my feelings and thoughts I gave you...

1720
01:41:44,510 --> 01:41:49,100
- It must be so hard to say that.
- She broke down.

1721
01:41:58,030 --> 01:42:02,840
- It felt like they all went to waste.
- Right.

1722
01:42:10,130 --> 01:42:13,480
After I heard that...

1723
01:42:14,640 --> 01:42:18,140
being face to face with you...

1724
01:42:20,750 --> 01:42:23,330
felt scary.

1725
01:42:23,330 --> 01:42:28,790
It could be frightening that
he could say it so easily.

1726
01:42:41,160 --> 01:42:44,140
I guess...

1727
01:42:47,670 --> 01:42:52,520
I was wondering if I could get
my feelings across...

1728
01:42:59,760 --> 01:43:06,850
[What should I say?]

1729
01:43:09,980 --> 01:43:12,850
So do you feel at ease right now?

1730
01:43:24,130 --> 01:43:31,050
Aigoo, she must feel embarrassed
for saying that in that situation.

1731
01:43:33,140 --> 01:43:36,460
First of all, the wording...

1732
01:43:37,730 --> 01:43:40,110
"At ease."

1733
01:43:42,900 --> 01:43:46,130
I didn't realize...

1734
01:43:47,200 --> 01:43:51,090
it would be so difficult for you.

1735
01:43:51,090 --> 01:43:55,920
I didn't know, but I think it was
a selfish way to say it.

1736
01:43:55,920 --> 01:44:02,310
I didn't realize my words would
have such an impact.

1737
01:44:10,940 --> 01:44:15,490
I can see how that was tough for you.

1738
01:44:21,200 --> 01:44:25,390
I didn't know that you were
struggling because of that.

1739
01:44:27,520 --> 01:44:30,120
I hurt you unintentionally.

1740
01:44:38,330 --> 01:44:39,860
I'm sorry.

1741
01:44:47,110 --> 01:44:49,610
Honestly, I feel so empty.

1742
01:44:51,280 --> 01:44:54,320
After I said that? What I said?

1743
01:44:54,320 --> 01:45:00,710
I know how she feels. She's been so devoted.

1744
01:45:06,360 --> 01:45:08,690
It's not what you said.

1745
01:45:08,690 --> 01:45:11,930
Sure, it's not because of those words.

1746
01:45:13,250 --> 01:45:17,440
Every moment, since Japan...

1747
01:45:17,440 --> 01:45:22,450
Every moment
where I expressed how I was feeling.

1748
01:45:26,150 --> 01:45:29,610
I thought my feelings were communicated.

1749
01:45:29,610 --> 01:45:31,360
Were they?

1750
01:45:31,360 --> 01:45:33,430
Yes, of course.

1751
01:45:33,430 --> 01:45:35,830
Right.

1752
01:45:35,830 --> 01:45:38,870
- Of course they were.
- Okay.

1753
01:45:40,000 --> 01:45:42,180
That's good, then.

1754
01:45:48,270 --> 01:45:50,730
[Fidgeting]

1755
01:45:54,050 --> 01:45:56,520
Seong Min must feel so frustrated, too.

1756
01:45:56,520 --> 01:45:59,280
He feels bad, but he doesn't
know what he did wrong.

1757
01:45:59,280 --> 01:46:02,410
- He doesn't know.
- Their personalities are just so different.

1758
01:46:02,410 --> 01:46:06,280
Let's go. Do you have anything else to say?

1759
01:46:18,690 --> 01:46:20,560
- Let's go.
- Okay.

1760
01:46:30,450 --> 01:46:36,420
[The two head out in somber vibes]

1761
01:46:36,420 --> 01:46:39,080
Min Ju did so well.

1762
01:46:40,850 --> 01:46:42,600
That's how you date.

1763
01:46:42,600 --> 01:46:45,810
When you express your emotions,

1764
01:46:45,810 --> 01:46:48,715
people tend to be embarrassed
about being sad.

1765
01:46:48,715 --> 01:46:49,455
Right.

1766
01:46:49,455 --> 01:46:55,245
It's good to be open about it like that.

1767
01:47:00,840 --> 01:47:07,870
[Silence in the car]

1768
01:47:15,010 --> 01:47:17,370
They just feel emotions so differently.

1769
01:47:17,370 --> 01:47:24,380
[Min Ju turns her back]

1770
01:47:26,400 --> 01:47:28,120
[Glancing]

1771
01:47:30,540 --> 01:47:34,620
Wow, we haven't seen a scene this cold yet.

1772
01:47:35,900 --> 01:47:41,440
[They arrive at the house]

1773
01:47:42,190 --> 01:47:45,430
- This is hard for Min Ju, too.
- Right.

1774
01:47:49,590 --> 01:47:55,280
It's not like
I've had a lot of time to think,

1775
01:47:57,310 --> 01:48:03,310
but I think what you're saying is,
it's not about the wording.

1776
01:48:03,310 --> 01:48:05,040
I think...

1777
01:48:06,260 --> 01:48:09,180
because of that moment,

1778
01:48:09,180 --> 01:48:15,120
all the effort you made,
all the feelings you shared,

1779
01:48:15,120 --> 01:48:20,140
felt like they disappeared for you.

1780
01:48:20,140 --> 01:48:22,470
How should I say this...

1781
01:48:22,470 --> 01:48:27,150
No, I don't regret sharing my feelings.

1782
01:48:27,150 --> 01:48:29,750
But then now...

1783
01:48:32,860 --> 01:48:39,090
I was just curious what you were
thinking when you said that to me.

1784
01:48:39,090 --> 01:48:40,520
Right.

1785
01:48:40,520 --> 01:48:47,120
I thought maybe you wanted
to see me as soon as possible

1786
01:48:47,120 --> 01:48:51,170
to tell me what you realized,
and tie up loose ends.

1787
01:48:51,170 --> 01:48:55,380
Oh, I see. I...

1788
01:48:55,380 --> 01:48:59,340
It wasn't like that. Actually...

1789
01:48:59,340 --> 01:49:04,630
being at ease, tying up loose ends...

1790
01:49:05,510 --> 01:49:09,640
It's not like "This is how I feel.
I feel at ease."

1791
01:49:10,560 --> 01:49:13,600
I still have a lot of questions.

1792
01:49:15,580 --> 01:49:19,210
But you took me outside. So...

1793
01:49:19,210 --> 01:49:22,940
running, and feeling cathartic...

1794
01:49:22,940 --> 01:49:29,700
I felt so liberated
from what I've been feeling.

1795
01:49:29,700 --> 01:49:32,460
That whole situation made me feel at ease.

1796
01:49:32,460 --> 01:49:38,810
So, that's why I said that. But...

1797
01:49:40,510 --> 01:49:46,240
How do I say this? "I told you how I feel,
so now I'm going to do my thing."

1798
01:49:46,240 --> 01:49:51,050
That's how you took it, right?

1799
01:49:51,050 --> 01:49:54,340
I don't want you to take it that way.

1800
01:49:54,340 --> 01:50:01,320
But I'm sorry, and I feel sad
if that's how it made you feel.

1801
01:50:03,690 --> 01:50:09,290
I didn't think it could be misunderstood.

1802
01:50:10,840 --> 01:50:13,040
So, I misunderstood it?

1803
01:50:13,040 --> 01:50:18,420
I made you misconstrue it.
That's the right way to look at it.

1804
01:50:22,640 --> 01:50:26,370
But I don't know
how you're going to take this.

1805
01:50:31,660 --> 01:50:34,150
What I remember is...

1806
01:50:35,110 --> 01:50:38,000
I remember that I checked.

1807
01:50:38,000 --> 01:50:41,050
Do you feel at ease because
of what you said yesterday?

1808
01:50:41,050 --> 01:50:45,290
I remember that you said yes.

1809
01:50:45,290 --> 01:50:47,420
And when we went to the restaurant,

1810
01:50:47,420 --> 01:50:51,280
it felt like you wanted to quickly tell me

1811
01:50:51,280 --> 01:50:55,950
that you were done sorting your feelings.

1812
01:50:56,790 --> 01:51:01,040
It felt like you wanted to be done with it.

1813
01:51:01,040 --> 01:51:04,810
- To get it over with.
- That really upset me.

1814
01:51:04,810 --> 01:51:08,540
I'd rather all this be a misunderstanding.

1815
01:51:08,540 --> 01:51:12,530
You saying "I feel at ease"
at the Han River...

1816
01:51:12,530 --> 01:51:17,490
I wish you just felt good
about being at the river.

1817
01:51:20,980 --> 01:51:22,660
[Busy Hamster: I had fun thanks to you!]

1818
01:51:22,660 --> 01:51:24,660
[Get some rest and feel better tomorrow]

1819
01:51:25,460 --> 01:51:27,330
I'm rooting for
your new start at your job!]

1820
01:51:27,330 --> 01:51:29,140
[Good luck this week!]

1821
01:51:30,760 --> 01:51:34,050
[I'll never forget Tokushima!]

1822
01:51:34,050 --> 01:51:38,020
[Thanks for the memories,
and let's continue making them.]

1823
01:51:38,930 --> 01:51:45,450
[Every day goes by
so fast, wish I could freeze time]

1824
01:51:48,770 --> 01:51:54,090
[She does not want all
these feelings to have been fake]

1825
01:51:54,090 --> 01:51:57,160
She spent 100 of her energy, and it's gone.

1826
01:51:57,160 --> 01:52:00,040
I totally get it.

1827
01:52:00,040 --> 01:52:08,640
[Her feelings are exploding out of control]

1828
01:52:09,540 --> 01:52:16,330
[Can they close the distance
between them again?]

1829
01:52:16,330 --> 01:52:17,790
Don't cry...

1830
01:52:17,790 --> 01:52:20,650
You can't be misled
by having good conversations.

1831
01:52:20,650 --> 01:52:23,270
I don't even think
they have good conversations.

1832
01:52:23,270 --> 01:52:25,530
- Right.
- You're right.

1833
01:52:25,530 --> 01:52:26,930
They weren't a fit.

1834
01:52:26,930 --> 01:52:30,340
Min Ju was so devoted.

1835
01:52:30,340 --> 01:52:33,510
But her feelings were just kicked down.

1836
01:52:33,510 --> 01:52:38,270
She got fixated on the idea
that they were a fit.

1837
01:52:38,270 --> 01:52:40,760
She tried to accommodate that.

1838
01:52:40,760 --> 01:52:43,310
You have to apply what So Yun said.

1839
01:52:43,310 --> 01:52:47,060
She said she was stuck in the
"I only need three seconds."

1840
01:52:47,060 --> 01:52:48,870
Min Ju has to apply that to herself.

1841
01:52:48,870 --> 01:52:51,320
I know. I think so, too.

1842
01:52:52,100 --> 01:52:54,840
[The city lights have fallen tonight]

1843
01:52:54,840 --> 01:52:56,380
Who is that?

1844
01:52:57,600 --> 01:52:58,930
It's Wu Yeol.

1845
01:52:58,930 --> 01:53:01,670
- It's not Yu Gyeong.
- I'm so curious.

1846
01:53:07,650 --> 01:53:10,540
[His date is So Yun]

1847
01:53:10,540 --> 01:53:11,970
What?

1848
01:53:11,970 --> 01:53:13,600
So Yun goes, "What?"

1849
01:53:13,600 --> 01:53:16,590
- Did they pick each other?
- No way.

1850
01:53:18,700 --> 01:53:21,800
[Swings around]

1851
01:53:21,800 --> 01:53:23,470
What?

1852
01:53:23,470 --> 01:53:27,040
- Did you know who I was?
- As soon as I saw your bag...

1853
01:53:27,040 --> 01:53:29,610
I said, "Why is he there?"

1854
01:53:29,610 --> 01:53:32,530
Why is Wu Yeol there?

1855
01:53:32,530 --> 01:53:35,280
I didn't think this would happen.

1856
01:53:35,280 --> 01:53:37,660
I was not expecting this.

1857
01:53:37,660 --> 01:53:40,580
I had no idea you would show up.

1858
01:53:40,580 --> 01:53:43,930
- Wu Yeol is surprised.
- I didn't know it would be you.

1859
01:53:43,930 --> 01:53:46,610
This is so funny.

1860
01:53:47,940 --> 01:53:52,190
[A text arrives]

1861
01:53:52,190 --> 01:53:54,900
- What does this mean?
- I know, what is it?

1862
01:53:54,900 --> 01:53:58,880
We weren't matched with the
"person who changed me."

1863
01:53:59,580 --> 01:54:02,740
The person who changed me the most...

1864
01:54:02,740 --> 01:54:05,280
is Yu Gyeong, but...

1865
01:54:06,250 --> 01:54:12,180
- I think Seo Won is the right choice.
- Seo Won.

1866
01:54:12,180 --> 01:54:13,820
[They failed to be matched]

1867
01:54:13,820 --> 01:54:17,670
- I see. They didn't get matched.
- It's the people who were left behind.

1868
01:54:17,670 --> 01:54:19,990
We weren't expecting each other...

1869
01:54:19,990 --> 01:54:23,440
- because we were left behind.
- What is this?

1870
01:54:23,440 --> 01:54:27,330
"Try to make positive changes
in one another."

1871
01:54:27,330 --> 01:54:29,990
Should we try to make positive changes, then?

1872
01:54:29,990 --> 01:54:31,940
Let's try it.

1873
01:54:31,940 --> 01:54:35,040
- So who got matched?
- For us...

1874
01:54:36,300 --> 01:54:38,700
- I see.
- Who got matched?

1875
01:54:38,700 --> 01:54:41,170
Besides us two, the other six?

1876
01:54:42,140 --> 01:54:45,130
I'm so curious. I need to see them tonight.

1877
01:54:45,130 --> 01:54:48,230
I suddenly have a rush of dopamine.

1878
01:54:48,230 --> 01:54:50,420
Let's get some chicken first.

1879
01:54:50,420 --> 01:54:52,450
We need chicken.

1880
01:54:52,450 --> 01:54:55,220
Wu Yeol must be anxious.

1881
01:54:55,220 --> 01:54:57,330
Right, Wu Yeol is anxious.

1882
01:54:57,330 --> 01:55:00,150
He's focused on Jun Hyeon.

1883
01:55:00,150 --> 01:55:02,220
Daebak. Of all people.

1884
01:55:02,220 --> 01:55:05,309
Let's enjoy some chicken.

1885
01:55:05,309 --> 01:55:08,076
These two are totally done with one another.

1886
01:55:08,076 --> 01:55:09,695
Completely.

1887
01:55:11,445 --> 01:55:13,240
So many options.

1888
01:55:13,240 --> 01:55:16,790
Let's definitely get the golden olive one.

1889
01:55:16,790 --> 01:55:18,510
Sounds good.

1890
01:55:20,780 --> 01:55:23,120
- Cheese balls?
- I love cheese balls.

1891
01:55:23,120 --> 01:55:25,520
- Draft beer?
- Yes.

1892
01:55:26,550 --> 01:55:28,040
Get two.

1893
01:55:29,290 --> 01:55:32,850
What do you think "being matched" means?

1894
01:55:32,850 --> 01:55:36,270
Maybe people who picked each other?

1895
01:55:36,270 --> 01:55:39,820
Really? So we picked different people?

1896
01:55:39,820 --> 01:55:41,290
That's right.

1897
01:55:41,290 --> 01:55:45,660
This is confusing me once again.

1898
01:55:45,660 --> 01:55:48,000
I'm going to struggle again.

1899
01:55:49,460 --> 01:55:51,230
- Cheers.
- Looks good.

1900
01:55:51,230 --> 01:55:53,880
Draft beer sounds so good.

1901
01:55:55,370 --> 01:55:58,140
[Chugging]

1902
01:55:58,140 --> 01:55:59,390
[The chicken arrives]

1903
01:55:59,390 --> 01:56:01,450
Thank you!

1904
01:56:02,880 --> 01:56:05,560
- I'm so hungry.
- That looks so good.

1905
01:56:05,560 --> 01:56:09,300
Let's eat. Food first.

1906
01:56:09,300 --> 01:56:12,110
- It's so tender.
- It looks so good.

1907
01:56:12,110 --> 01:56:14,600
Aren't we supposed to grab and rip?

1908
01:56:14,600 --> 01:56:18,030
Right. Want me to do one for you?

1909
01:56:19,030 --> 01:56:21,040
[Demonstrated by an experienced teacher]

1910
01:56:21,040 --> 01:56:23,240
Looks good.

1911
01:56:23,240 --> 01:56:24,450
Yum.

1912
01:56:24,450 --> 01:56:29,560
[Forgetting about reality for
a second, immersed in chicken]

1913
01:56:30,760 --> 01:56:33,110
But seriously.

1914
01:56:33,110 --> 01:56:36,320
That conversation was huge for me, too.

1915
01:56:36,320 --> 01:56:39,340
- Right.
- It feels easy.

1916
01:56:39,340 --> 01:56:43,150
I didn't know we could be
this cool with one another.

1917
01:56:43,150 --> 01:56:46,940
- It's nice.
- It is.

1918
01:56:46,940 --> 01:56:49,760
I wasn't trying to eat so well.

1919
01:56:50,530 --> 01:56:52,120
You look good.

1920
01:56:53,630 --> 01:56:56,220
I didn't want to look good.

1921
01:56:56,220 --> 01:56:58,280
Then you don't.

1922
01:56:58,280 --> 01:56:59,440
[Cracking up]

1923
01:57:02,560 --> 01:57:04,410
In your opinion,

1924
01:57:05,370 --> 01:57:09,030
what do you think I should do?

1925
01:57:09,030 --> 01:57:10,640
Strategy?

1926
01:57:10,640 --> 01:57:14,490
You kept saying, liking someone
as a person is different than

1927
01:57:14,490 --> 01:57:16,480
liking someone as a partner.

1928
01:57:18,920 --> 01:57:23,530
But I always wondered
if you could break out of that.

1929
01:57:23,530 --> 01:57:25,370
That locks you in.

1930
01:57:25,370 --> 01:57:30,440
- I'm curious who you have the most fun with.
- Right.

1931
01:57:31,870 --> 01:57:33,880
How do I feel?

1932
01:57:34,800 --> 01:57:39,440
- I kept asking myself...
- What?

1933
01:57:39,440 --> 01:57:43,240
Who do I actually like?

1934
01:57:43,240 --> 01:57:45,930
Who am I the happiest with?

1935
01:57:45,930 --> 01:57:50,710
And what version of myself
do I like the most?

1936
01:57:50,710 --> 01:57:53,150
Considering all that, it was Yu Gyeong.

1937
01:57:53,150 --> 01:57:55,540
- Right.
- He's honest.

1938
01:57:55,540 --> 01:57:59,000
Aigoo, you've lost the cow,
but you're fixing the barn.

1939
01:57:59,000 --> 01:58:03,330
That's what I thought,
and I thought about it again.

1940
01:58:03,330 --> 01:58:06,300
I'm not certain how Yu Gyeong feels,

1941
01:58:06,300 --> 01:58:09,350
and I can't speak for her.

1942
01:58:10,330 --> 01:58:14,610
But she's confident about her own feelings.

1943
01:58:15,310 --> 01:58:19,950
She's not someone who would
lose those feelings.

1944
01:58:19,950 --> 01:58:21,610
Right.

1945
01:58:21,610 --> 01:58:25,380
So, do you think you have
a grasp on how she feels?

1946
01:58:25,380 --> 01:58:29,680
But when I see her? I have
no idea what she's thinking.

1947
01:58:29,680 --> 01:58:32,700
But the 1-on-1 conversations...

1948
01:58:32,700 --> 01:58:36,000
The 1-on-1 conversations

1949
01:58:37,750 --> 01:58:42,390
have never made me anxious.

1950
01:58:43,480 --> 01:58:46,290
But he's anxious now.

1951
01:58:46,290 --> 01:58:47,840
You look more anxious than anyone.

1952
01:58:47,840 --> 01:58:50,800
- Really?
- So Yun gets it.

1953
01:58:50,800 --> 01:58:53,330
- He's so anxious.
- I'm anxious.

1954
01:58:54,130 --> 01:58:57,780
Why is today's match bothering me so much?

1955
01:58:57,780 --> 01:58:59,360
Of course it is.

1956
01:58:59,360 --> 01:59:01,150
For me...

1957
01:59:03,190 --> 01:59:10,290
my feelings are in the certainty stage.

1958
01:59:10,290 --> 01:59:17,100
But this is happening with three days left?

1959
01:59:17,100 --> 01:59:21,010
- It's going to bother me.
- Right.

1960
01:59:21,010 --> 01:59:23,360
But I had this thought.

1961
01:59:23,360 --> 01:59:25,510
I should have done better while I had her.

1962
01:59:25,510 --> 01:59:28,410
I mean... I mean, you two...

1963
01:59:29,350 --> 01:59:32,550
- You had a whole relationship.
- I know.

1964
01:59:32,550 --> 01:59:36,110
I'm going to talk to Yu Gyeong a lot.

1965
01:59:38,970 --> 01:59:42,780
I'm trying to express myself as much as I can

1966
01:59:42,780 --> 01:59:45,580
and I think I've done a lot more
than I have before.

1967
01:59:45,580 --> 01:59:48,220
So, I think...

1968
01:59:48,920 --> 01:59:52,770
- the choice is Yu Gyeong's.
- Right.

1969
01:59:53,640 --> 01:59:55,750
I think it's out of my hands now.

1970
01:59:55,750 --> 02:00:01,260
Right. Wu Yeol is objective. He's great.

1971
02:00:01,260 --> 02:00:05,220
But emotionally, it's still tough.

1972
02:00:05,220 --> 02:00:07,090
Since we all live together.

1973
02:00:08,230 --> 02:00:13,510
[He hopes she feels the same,
but anxiety grows]

1974
02:00:13,510 --> 02:00:17,410
She might have been hurt by you

1975
02:00:17,410 --> 02:00:19,930
but she is capable of understanding you.

1976
02:00:19,930 --> 02:00:24,420
So Yun always has the best answers.

1977
02:00:24,420 --> 02:00:25,910
Right.

1978
02:00:30,320 --> 02:00:32,670
Thank you. That means a lot.

1979
02:00:32,670 --> 02:00:34,260
Got it?

1980
02:00:35,400 --> 02:00:37,030
Wow.

1981
02:00:37,030 --> 02:00:40,870
You're the only one who gets it.

1982
02:00:43,290 --> 02:00:44,750
Thank you.

1983
02:00:45,530 --> 02:00:47,640
I mean it.

1984
02:00:47,640 --> 02:00:51,810
Then, treat me to something after the show.

1985
02:00:51,810 --> 02:00:53,670
Of course.

1986
02:00:53,670 --> 02:00:56,470
I'll take you to this pocha.

1987
02:00:56,470 --> 02:00:58,720
I'm supposed to go with Jun Hyeon.

1988
02:00:59,390 --> 02:01:02,270
- She's the best!
- Do your thing, then.

1989
02:01:02,270 --> 02:01:06,430
[He feels better talking about his struggles]

1990
02:01:06,430 --> 02:01:07,710
That was so nice to see.

1991
02:01:07,710 --> 02:01:11,000
What did Wu Yeol look like
after he failed to be matched?

1992
02:01:11,000 --> 02:01:13,300
That was the first time he looked sad.

1993
02:01:13,300 --> 02:01:15,980
- So human.
- Human and cute.

1994
02:01:15,980 --> 02:01:17,810
He was jealous.

1995
02:01:17,810 --> 02:01:20,640
As soon as the match failed,
he wondered, "Who is Yu Gyeong with?"

1996
02:01:20,640 --> 02:01:21,700
He was anxious.

1997
02:01:21,700 --> 02:01:26,610
I like seeing these natural feelings
of jealousy in him.

1998
02:01:26,610 --> 02:01:28,550
Right.

1999
02:01:29,550 --> 02:01:33,440
- I'm so glad we came here.
- Should we go get dinner?

2000
02:01:33,440 --> 02:01:36,280
It's a different kind of happiness
than being with Wu Yeol.

2001
02:01:36,280 --> 02:01:38,780
After what you said,

2002
02:01:38,780 --> 02:01:41,850
I can't not open the door for you.

2003
02:01:41,850 --> 02:01:43,000
I have butterflies.

2004
02:01:43,000 --> 02:01:44,950
I'm starving.

2005
02:01:44,950 --> 02:01:47,210
I'm going to order four things today.

2006
02:01:47,210 --> 02:01:49,230
You usually get four things.

2007
02:01:50,130 --> 02:01:52,540
You always get four things.

2008
02:01:52,540 --> 02:01:55,110
Why are you saying it like you never do?

2009
02:01:55,110 --> 02:01:57,150
They're so happy together.

2010
02:01:57,150 --> 02:01:59,690
I'm a little embarrassed about my outfit.

2011
02:01:59,690 --> 02:02:01,740
- What? I'm sure she looks pretty.
- I've never seen this.

2012
02:02:01,740 --> 02:02:04,920
- I'm wearing a dress.
- Why is she wearing a dress?

2013
02:02:04,920 --> 02:02:08,660
- I'm so embarrassed.
- You're all dressed up.

2014
02:02:08,660 --> 02:02:10,330
Yes, I totally dressed up.

2015
02:02:10,330 --> 02:02:11,880
It looks nice.

2016
02:02:11,880 --> 02:02:14,050
I only wear it when I'm with you.

2017
02:02:14,050 --> 02:02:16,060
That's what happens.

2018
02:02:17,180 --> 02:02:19,690
He can't stay still!

2019
02:02:19,690 --> 02:02:21,850
They have outside seats, too.

2020
02:02:21,850 --> 02:02:24,200
Do you like sitting in the patio?

2021
02:02:24,200 --> 02:02:28,352
I love it. I'm a huge fan. I try to.

2022
02:02:28,352 --> 02:02:31,189
- Even when it's hot out,
- Really?

2023
02:02:31,189 --> 02:02:32,690
I try to go outside.

2024
02:02:32,690 --> 02:02:36,230
- I was at a cafe the other day...
- Was there a patio?

2025
02:02:36,230 --> 02:02:39,770
I sat at the patio,
and the vibes were amazing.

2026
02:02:39,770 --> 02:02:41,380
Look at this.

2027
02:02:41,380 --> 02:02:44,940
- I just sat outside like this.
- What in the world?

2028
02:02:48,060 --> 02:02:51,960
[Oops, reveals photo taken with Wu Yeol]

2029
02:02:53,560 --> 02:02:56,800
[Chaos]

2030
02:02:57,320 --> 02:02:59,340
I've seen pictures of you...

2031
02:03:00,060 --> 02:03:02,460
- I'm sorry.
- No, no, it could happen.

2032
02:03:02,460 --> 02:03:05,150
I've seen pictures of you
on Min Ju's phone, too.

2033
02:03:05,150 --> 02:03:07,060
No, no, no.

2034
02:03:07,060 --> 02:03:08,810
That's different.

2035
02:03:08,810 --> 02:03:12,390
- That is different.
- It happens.

2036
02:03:12,390 --> 02:03:14,260
I was careless.

2037
02:03:14,260 --> 02:03:16,790
No, no. It's okay. It happens.

2038
02:03:16,790 --> 02:03:18,570
It's really okay.

2039
02:03:21,420 --> 02:03:23,160
Where's our food?

2040
02:03:24,430 --> 02:03:27,170
They're like a comic book.

2041
02:03:27,940 --> 02:03:30,490
The basil is mine.

2042
02:03:34,500 --> 02:03:37,590
- My hands are shaking.
- They can't stop smiling.

2043
02:03:38,370 --> 02:03:40,300
Thank you.

2044
02:03:44,570 --> 02:03:46,110
What?

2045
02:03:46,110 --> 02:03:48,030
Delicious.

2046
02:03:48,030 --> 02:03:51,260
Everything is so delicious. The whole world.

2047
02:03:51,260 --> 02:03:52,200
Thank you.

2048
02:03:52,200 --> 02:03:55,650
Being so natural for him to take
care of her. That's powerful.

2049
02:03:55,650 --> 02:03:57,260
- Thank you.
- True.

2050
02:03:58,030 --> 02:04:03,720
You said
you don't have a big interest in food.

2051
02:04:03,720 --> 02:04:06,840
Me? I think I'm kind of into it these days.

2052
02:04:06,840 --> 02:04:08,520
You're eating so well.

2053
02:04:08,520 --> 02:04:10,680
I think I've been eating so well recently.

2054
02:04:10,680 --> 02:04:13,640
- You too? I think so.
- I am.

2055
02:04:13,640 --> 02:04:17,470
Right, he can accommodate Yu Gyeong.

2056
02:04:17,470 --> 02:04:19,820
He's smiling so much.

2057
02:04:19,820 --> 02:04:21,750
Do you like broccoli?

2058
02:04:21,750 --> 02:04:26,310
No. I don't really want to eat it.

2059
02:04:27,720 --> 02:04:29,840
Broccoli is good.

2060
02:04:34,630 --> 02:04:36,400
I'll try.

2061
02:04:51,130 --> 02:04:52,910
It's not bad.

2062
02:04:54,090 --> 02:04:56,280
It's crunchy.

2063
02:05:01,990 --> 02:05:05,070
If you have a crush on someone,
do you tell your mom?

2064
02:05:05,070 --> 02:05:07,830
This is how I tell my mom.

2065
02:05:07,830 --> 02:05:10,710
You know, that doesn't happen to her anymore.

2066
02:05:10,710 --> 02:05:13,780
So I tell her like I'm telling a funny story.

2067
02:05:13,780 --> 02:05:16,810
- How does she react?
- She gets excited.

2068
02:05:16,810 --> 02:05:19,020
She's close to her mom.

2069
02:05:19,020 --> 02:05:26,360
If you ask her for advice, does she tell you?

2070
02:05:26,360 --> 02:05:29,320
- Actually, my dad...
- You tell your dad?

2071
02:05:29,320 --> 02:05:30,660
- Really?
- Yes.

2072
02:05:30,660 --> 02:05:31,690
A close-knit family.

2073
02:05:31,690 --> 02:05:32,870
Your dad would hate that.

2074
02:05:32,870 --> 02:05:34,330
- He hates everyone.
- Right.

2075
02:05:34,330 --> 02:05:38,160
But he's rational about it.

2076
02:05:38,160 --> 02:05:41,490
I tend to listen to him.

2077
02:05:42,280 --> 02:05:43,610
Do you show them pictures?

2078
02:05:43,610 --> 02:05:44,920
Of course.

2079
02:05:44,920 --> 02:05:47,590
Do they sometimes not like how they look?

2080
02:05:47,590 --> 02:05:51,710
Yes. My dad even comments on their names.

2081
02:05:51,710 --> 02:05:53,420
Just their names?

2082
02:05:53,420 --> 02:05:54,850
Just by hearing the name?

2083
02:05:54,850 --> 02:05:58,550
He starts with, "That's a good name."

2084
02:06:00,240 --> 02:06:02,190
Even when I came here,

2085
02:06:02,190 --> 02:06:07,730
I was talking to my dad
at a Chinese restaurant,

2086
02:06:07,730 --> 02:06:10,760
and I kept losing confidence in myself.

2087
02:06:10,760 --> 02:06:13,440
Because he's usually right?

2088
02:06:13,440 --> 02:06:15,990
I didn't think so,

2089
02:06:15,990 --> 02:06:18,750
but my dad already knew.

2090
02:06:18,750 --> 02:06:21,880
I thought,
I really have no judgment of character.

2091
02:06:22,680 --> 02:06:28,050
I was worried, what if I don't see
clearly on the show?

2092
02:06:28,050 --> 02:06:31,380
He said, he doesn't know that, either.

2093
02:06:31,380 --> 02:06:32,400
Really?

2094
02:06:32,400 --> 02:06:35,370
He said even if you look,
if someone wants to hide...

2095
02:06:35,370 --> 02:06:39,940
Right, if they're determined to hide,
you can't see.

2096
02:06:39,940 --> 02:06:44,460
You had that conversation
with your dad before you came?

2097
02:06:46,090 --> 02:06:47,660
I rely on him a lot.

2098
02:06:47,660 --> 02:06:51,250
A lot. I think I rely a lot on others.

2099
02:06:55,390 --> 02:06:57,910
- My clothes are tight.
- Because you're full?

2100
02:06:57,910 --> 02:07:00,050
I might pop.

2101
02:07:01,110 --> 02:07:02,880
We finished all the food.

2102
02:07:05,830 --> 02:07:08,480
- Thank you for the food!
- Thank you for the food.

2103
02:07:08,480 --> 02:07:09,990
I think she's into him.

2104
02:07:09,990 --> 02:07:11,880
He's so cool.

2105
02:07:11,880 --> 02:07:13,690
It was delicious.

2106
02:07:13,690 --> 02:07:16,800
[Oh, my gosh]

2107
02:07:16,800 --> 02:07:19,770
I'm rooting for them!

2108
02:07:19,770 --> 02:07:21,830
Comparing this to her dates with Wu Yeol...

2109
02:07:21,830 --> 02:07:23,620
They're different genre movies.

2110
02:07:23,620 --> 02:07:25,800
Rom-coms with different backgrounds.

2111
02:07:25,800 --> 02:07:26,850
So different.

2112
02:07:26,850 --> 02:07:30,170
Jun Hyeon's biggest strength is...

2113
02:07:30,170 --> 02:07:34,950
that he doesn't have big mood swings.

2114
02:07:34,950 --> 02:07:38,480
I know he wants to get up and run toward her,

2115
02:07:38,480 --> 02:07:40,720
but he stays still. He doesn't get up.

2116
02:07:40,720 --> 02:07:43,720
- He doesn't boil nor freeze.
- He smiles softly.

2117
02:07:43,720 --> 02:07:47,380
I think Yu Gyeong likes him
more than we expected.

2118
02:07:47,380 --> 02:07:48,740
That's what I'm saying!

2119
02:07:48,740 --> 02:07:52,300
She said, "I'm so talkative around you."

2120
02:07:52,300 --> 02:07:54,430
He listens to her.

2121
02:07:54,430 --> 02:07:55,970
This is the situation right now.

2122
02:07:55,970 --> 02:07:59,940
We're watching soccer, and there
are five minutes of extra time.

2123
02:07:59,940 --> 02:08:03,670
Wu Yeol is anxious,
as if he's going to concede a goal.

2124
02:08:03,670 --> 02:08:08,170
Jun Hyeon is using most
of that time until the end.

2125
02:08:08,170 --> 02:08:11,440
That's working on Yu Gyeong.

2126
02:08:11,440 --> 02:08:16,830
He said the best line I've heard
this season of Heart Signal.

2127
02:08:16,830 --> 02:08:20,350
Jun Hyeon said, "It's not
romance without extravagance."

2128
02:08:20,350 --> 02:08:21,640
"It's not romance without extravagance."

2129
02:08:21,640 --> 02:08:24,240
The fact that she put on a dress.

2130
02:08:24,240 --> 02:08:29,370
It's huge for a woman
to put on a fancy dress.

2131
02:08:29,370 --> 02:08:31,280
It's huge.

2132
02:08:31,280 --> 02:08:33,042
I'm only going to wear suits from now on.

2133
02:08:33,042 --> 02:08:36,613
Weren't we leaning toward Wu Yeol last week?

2134
02:08:36,613 --> 02:08:38,600
- Completely.
- How does it feel today?

2135
02:08:38,600 --> 02:08:41,200
- The tables have turned.
- I want to root for them.

2136
02:08:41,200 --> 02:08:44,410
- It's 50-50 now.
- 50-50 is huge.

2137
02:08:44,410 --> 02:08:46,220
That's huge.

2138
02:08:46,220 --> 02:08:48,870
We don't know who she will choose now.

2139
02:08:48,870 --> 02:08:51,750
We might not see each other.

2140
02:08:52,610 --> 02:08:55,060
I wish you the best until the end.

2141
02:08:55,060 --> 02:08:57,470
Even if I get hurt...

2142
02:08:58,620 --> 02:09:00,200
Min Ju?

2143
02:09:00,200 --> 02:09:03,940
- It's hard because they're so different.
- You're right.

2144
02:09:03,940 --> 02:09:06,050
I'm still thinking.

2145
02:09:06,930 --> 02:09:10,040
One of them is totally all in.

2146
02:09:10,040 --> 02:09:11,480
Yu Gyeong?

2147
02:09:11,480 --> 02:09:14,750
Can I stay on this rollercoaster?

2148
02:09:14,750 --> 02:09:17,730
- Are you feeling down?
- Feeling down?

2149
02:09:20,960 --> 02:09:25,350
He's someone who can do anything with trust.

2150
02:09:25,350 --> 02:09:29,550
I'm scared, but I'm choosing that path.

2151
02:09:30,810 --> 02:09:34,880
I knew Jun Hyeon would recognize me.

2152
02:09:34,880 --> 02:09:38,110
With Wu Yeol, it was "Would he?"

2153
02:09:38,110 --> 02:09:40,280
I had so many mixed feelings.

2154
02:09:41,030 --> 02:09:44,770
I developed feelings
without even realizing it.

2155
02:09:44,770 --> 02:09:47,660
I was seeing what I couldn't see before.

2156
02:09:48,820 --> 02:09:51,900
I like what I'm feeling.

2157
02:09:53,250 --> 02:09:55,070
Did you think it would be me?

2158
02:09:55,070 --> 02:09:57,980
Yes. I knew it was you.

2159
02:09:57,980 --> 02:09:59,570
For me...
